WEBVTT

00:24.792 --> 00:28.096
* [ Woman Vocalizing ]

01:06.500 --> 01:08.469
[ Bird Squawking ]

01:08.502 --> 01:10.204
[ Dog Barking ]

01:10.238 --> 01:14.375
[ Girl ]
BUGLAR, MAKE IT STOP !
I CAN'T ! I CAN'T !

01:14.408 --> 01:16.777
PLEASE !
[ Crying ]
[ Boy Screaming ] MAMA !

01:16.810 --> 01:19.647
[ Dog Growling,
Whimpering ]

01:19.680 --> 01:21.982
[ Screaming ]
MAKE IT STOP, PLEASE !

01:22.015 --> 01:26.354
[ Whimpering Continues ]
[ Boy ]
MAMA, HELP ME !

01:28.289 --> 01:30.624
[ Boy Screaming ]
[ Girl ]
HERE, BOY !

01:30.658 --> 01:32.826
[ Crying ]

01:32.860 --> 01:36.430
[ Whimpering Continues ]

01:40.168 --> 01:44.805
OH, GRANDMA BABY.
MMM-MM.

01:57.385 --> 01:59.019
SHH !

01:59.052 --> 02:02.790
WE'RE GONNA NEED SOME FOOD.
WAIT HERE.
OKAY.

02:08.061 --> 02:10.231
[ Here Boy Whimpering ]

02:12.666 --> 02:14.968
GOOD BOY,
HERE BOY.

02:36.757 --> 02:38.826
HOWARD, COME ON !

02:40.928 --> 02:44.532
COME ON.
HOWARD, BUGLAR !

02:44.565 --> 02:46.467
WHERE YOU GOIN' ?

02:46.500 --> 02:47.901
BYE, DENVER.
BYE ?

02:49.670 --> 02:52.273
[ Gasps ]
WE GOTTA GO !

02:55.509 --> 02:58.546
[ Crying ]
BUGLAR, COME ON.

02:58.579 --> 03:02.416
NO !
BUGE !
GO AHEAD.

03:02.450 --> 03:04.785
HOWARD !

03:17.398 --> 03:20.100
NOW WHAT'D YOU GO
AND DO THAT FOR ?

03:22.303 --> 03:24.272
[ Panting ]

03:30.811 --> 03:32.980
MAMA.

04:03.577 --> 04:06.980
[ Hoofbeats Clattering ]

04:09.483 --> 04:12.185
* [ Woman Vocalizing ]

04:54.395 --> 04:57.365
[ Barking ]

04:58.332 --> 05:01.369
WATCH OUT THERE,
HERE BOY.

05:01.402 --> 05:03.537
[ Child Crying ]

05:19.687 --> 05:21.689
[ Barking ]

05:58.392 --> 06:00.561
PAUL ?

06:02.362 --> 06:04.264
PAUL D ?

06:05.132 --> 06:08.101
IS THAT YOU ?

06:08.135 --> 06:10.003
WHAT'S LEFT.

06:10.037 --> 06:14.207
[ Hoofbeats Clattering ]

06:14.241 --> 06:17.711
HOW YOU BEEN, GIRL ?
BESIDES BAREFOOT.

06:19.980 --> 06:22.616
MESSED UP MY LEGS
BACK YONDER.

06:22.650 --> 06:24.384
CHAMOMILE.

06:24.418 --> 06:26.787
I DON'T EVEN
WANNA HEAR ABOUT IT.

06:26.820 --> 06:28.789
I ALWAYS DID HATE
THAT STUFF.

06:28.822 --> 06:31.625
YOU'RE LOOKIN' GOOD.

06:31.659 --> 06:34.127
DEVIL'S CONFUSION, SETHE.

06:34.161 --> 06:38.766
HE LETS ME LOOK GOOD
AS LONG AS I FEEL BAD.

06:38.799 --> 06:41.469
HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN ?

06:46.574 --> 06:48.108
EIGHTEEN YEARS.

06:50.243 --> 06:52.480
EIGHTEEN YEARS ?

06:52.513 --> 06:57.317
I SWEAR, I'VE BEEN WALKIN'
EVERY ONE OF 'EM.

06:57.350 --> 07:01.288
MIND IF I JOIN YOU ?
YOU WANNA SOAK 'EM ?
LET ME GET YOU SOME WATER.

07:01.321 --> 07:03.991
NO. CAN'T BABY FEET.

07:04.024 --> 07:07.628
THEY'S GOT A WHOLE LOT MORE
TRAMPLIN' TO DO.

07:07.661 --> 07:09.497
[ Sighing ]

07:09.530 --> 07:13.000
YOU AIN'T
LEAVIN' RIGHT AWAY.
YOU STAY AWHILE.

07:13.033 --> 07:16.804
AH, WELL, LONG ENOUGH
TO SEE BABY SUGGS...

07:16.837 --> 07:19.139
AND YOU.

07:19.172 --> 07:21.609
WHERE IS SHE ?

07:21.642 --> 07:23.043
DEAD.

07:26.514 --> 07:28.181
OH, NO.

07:28.215 --> 07:32.520
WHEN ?
EIGHT YEARS AGO
NOW.

07:32.553 --> 07:34.688
ALMOST NINE.

07:34.722 --> 07:39.693
WAS IT HARD ? I HOPE
SHE DIDN'T DIE HARD.

07:39.727 --> 07:42.295
SOFT AS CREAM.

07:42.329 --> 07:45.533
BEIN' ALIVE
WAS THE HARD PART.

07:45.566 --> 07:48.201
SORRY YOU MISSED HER,
THOUGH.

07:48.235 --> 07:50.538
IS THAT WHAT
YOU CAME BY FOR ?

07:52.172 --> 07:55.509
THAT'S SOME
OF WHAT I CAME FOR.

07:55.543 --> 07:57.210
REST IS YOU.

08:00.047 --> 08:03.851
[ Sighs ]
TRUTH BE KNOWN,

08:03.884 --> 08:07.588
THESE DAYS I GO ANYWHERE
THEY LET ME SIT DOWN.

08:10.758 --> 08:15.896
I WOULDN'T HAVE TO ASK YOU
ABOUT HI M, WOULD I ?

08:15.929 --> 08:19.567
YOU'D TELL ME IF
THERE WAS ANYTHING TO TELL,
WOULDN'T YOU ?

08:19.600 --> 08:23.236
I'D TELL YOU.
YOU KNOW I WOULD.

08:23.270 --> 08:25.272
SO YOU DON'T KNOW
NOTHIN' EITHER.

08:27.274 --> 08:32.645
[ Sighs ]
HALLE, HALLE.
[ Grunts ]

08:32.679 --> 08:34.847
[ Horse Whinnying ]

08:48.796 --> 08:50.798
WE GOT SPARE ROOMS.

08:52.465 --> 08:55.268
COULD STAY THE NIGHT
IF YOU HAD THE MIND TO.

08:55.302 --> 08:57.370
YOU DON'T SOUND TOO STEADY
IN THE OFFER.

08:57.404 --> 09:00.407
OH, IT'S TRULY MEANT.

09:00.440 --> 09:02.743
IT'S JUST THAT I HOPE
YOU'LL PARDON MY HOUSE.

09:02.776 --> 09:04.645
"MY HOUSE."

09:07.214 --> 09:10.550
I LIKE THE SOUND OF THAT.

09:10.584 --> 09:12.152
COME ON IN.

09:18.258 --> 09:20.661
COME ON IN.
[ Chuckling ]

09:33.106 --> 09:37.377
GOOD GOD, GIRL.
WHAT KIND OF EVIL
YOU GOT IN THERE ?

09:37.410 --> 09:40.881
IT AIN'T EVIL.
JUST SAD. COME ON.

09:40.914 --> 09:43.183
STEP ON THROUGH.

10:53.320 --> 10:55.655
I-I THOUGHT YOU SAID
SHE DIED SOFT.

10:55.689 --> 10:59.292
THAT'S NOT BABY SUGGS.

10:59.326 --> 11:03.697
WHO THEN ?
MY DAUGHTER.

11:03.731 --> 11:07.901
THE ONE I SENT AHEAD WITH
THE BOYS BEFORE I RUN OFF.
SHE DIDN'T LIVE ?

11:07.935 --> 11:10.303
NO.
BOYS TOO ?

11:10.337 --> 11:12.405
NO, THEY ALIVE,
I PRAY.

11:12.439 --> 11:16.509
THEY RUN OFF JUST BEFORE
BABY SUGGS WENT AND DIED.

11:20.580 --> 11:23.583
PROBABLY BEST.
AHH !

11:23.616 --> 11:26.086
NEGRO BOY GOT LEGS,
HE OUGHT TO USE 'EM.

11:26.119 --> 11:30.657
SIT AROUND TOO LONG,
SOMEBODY'LL FIGURE OUT
A WAY TO TIE 'EM UP.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.060
AHH !

11:39.232 --> 11:42.169
BY YOURSELF, THEN ?
NO.

11:42.202 --> 11:45.072
GOT THE GIRL I WAS CARRYIN'
WHEN I LEFT SWEET HOME.

11:45.105 --> 11:51.011
YOU HAD THAT BABY, DID YOU ?
DAMN, I DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D MAKE IT.

11:51.044 --> 11:54.047
RUNNIN' OFF PREGNANT,
ALL BY YOURSELF TOO.

11:54.081 --> 11:56.449
[ Footsteps ]
DENVER !

11:58.819 --> 12:00.687
COME HERE, BABY.

12:00.720 --> 12:03.456
I WANT YOU TO MEET SOMEBODY.

12:06.226 --> 12:08.728
PAUL D, THIS HERE
IS MY DENVER.

12:13.500 --> 12:17.070
UH, MORNIN', MISS DENVER.
IT'S A PLEASURE.

12:24.177 --> 12:26.146
MORNIN', MR. D.

12:26.179 --> 12:30.984
UH, GARNER, BABY.
PAUL D GARNER.

12:31.018 --> 12:33.586
YES, SIR.
GLAD TO GET
A LOOK AT YOU.

12:33.620 --> 12:36.423
SHE A FINE-LOOKIN'
YOUNG LADY, SETHE.

12:36.456 --> 12:40.260
YEAH. GOT HER DADDY'S
SWEET FACE.

12:40.293 --> 12:41.594
YOU KNOW MY DADDY ?

12:41.628 --> 12:43.496
OF COURSE HE KNOW YOUR DADDY.

12:43.530 --> 12:45.899
HE FROM SWEET HOME.

12:45.933 --> 12:48.802
YEAH.

12:48.836 --> 12:51.771
SWEET HOME.

12:51.805 --> 12:56.009
HOW COME EVERYBODY WHO RUN OFF
FROM SWEET HOME CAN'T STOP
TALKIN' ABOUT IT ?

12:56.043 --> 12:59.446
IT LOOKS LIKE
IF IT WAS SO SWEET,
YOU WOULDN'T RUN AWAY.

12:59.479 --> 13:02.349
GIRL, WHO YOU THINK
YOU TALKIN' TO ?

13:02.382 --> 13:05.185
TRUE, TRUE.
SHE-SHE RIGHT, SETHE.

13:05.218 --> 13:09.656
IT WASN'T SWEET,
AND IT SURE WASN'T HOME.

13:09.689 --> 13:13.994
BUT IT'S WHERE WE WERE,
ALL TOGETHER.

13:14.027 --> 13:17.464
COME BACK WHETHER
WE WANTED TO OR NOT.

13:20.901 --> 13:22.135
[ Sighs ]

13:23.670 --> 13:25.772
WE HAVE A GHOST HERE,
YOU KNOW ?

13:25.805 --> 13:29.176
[ Liquid Pouring ]
WE MET.

13:29.209 --> 13:30.878
DENVER, HEAT UP THAT STOVE.

13:30.911 --> 13:34.481
CAN'T HAVE A FRIEND STOP BY
AND DON'T FEED HIM.

13:34.514 --> 13:37.117
OH, DON'T GO TO NO TROUBLE
ON MY ACCOUNT.

13:37.150 --> 13:39.452
BREAD AIN'T
NO TROUBLE.

13:39.486 --> 13:41.989
THE REST I BRING BACK
FROM WHERE I WORK.

13:42.022 --> 13:45.392
LEAST I CAN DO
WORKIN' DAWN TO NOON
IS BRING HOME SUPPER.

13:45.425 --> 13:47.327
GOT ANY OBJECTIONS
TO PIKE ?

13:47.360 --> 13:50.563
IF HE DON'T OBJECT TO ME,
I DON'T OBJECT TO HIM.

13:54.701 --> 13:57.070
WHY DON'T YOU SPEND THE NIGHT,
MR. GARNER ?

13:57.104 --> 14:00.840
THAT WAY, TWO OF YOU
CAN TALK ABOUT SWEET HOME
ALL NIGHT LONG.

14:00.874 --> 14:03.410
DENVER, WHAT IS THE MATTER
WITH YOU ?

14:03.443 --> 14:05.745
I NEVER KNOWN YOU
TO BEHAVE THIS WAY.

14:05.778 --> 14:07.780
[ Crying ]

14:09.382 --> 14:13.253
[ Sniffling ]
MAMA, I CAN'T NO MORE.

14:13.286 --> 14:15.088
[ Sniffling Continues ]

14:16.356 --> 14:18.091
I CAN'T NO MORE.

14:18.125 --> 14:20.393
YOU CAN'T WHAT ?
WHAT CAN'T YOU ?

14:20.427 --> 14:22.129
CAN'T LIVE HERE.

14:24.431 --> 14:27.500
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE I'M GONNA GO
OR WHAT I'M GONNA DO,

14:27.534 --> 14:29.836
BUT I CAN'T STAY HERE !

14:29.869 --> 14:32.505
[ Sobbing ]

14:32.539 --> 14:35.608
NOBODY SPEAKS TO US,
NOBODY COMES BY,

14:35.642 --> 14:39.512
NOBODY EVEN KNOWS
I'M ALIVE.

14:39.546 --> 14:41.614
OH, DENVER.

14:41.648 --> 14:43.483
COME HERE, BABY.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.587
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
SETHE.

14:47.620 --> 14:50.590
I'M A GROWN MAN...

14:50.623 --> 14:53.293
WITH NOTHIN' NEW
LEFT TO SEE OR DO,

14:53.326 --> 14:55.562
BUT I TELL YOU
IT CAN'T BE EASY,

14:55.595 --> 14:58.198
A YOUNG GIRL
LIVIN' IN A HAUNTED PLACE.

14:58.231 --> 15:00.533
MAYBE YOU OUGHT
TO MOVE.

15:00.567 --> 15:02.469
NO.

15:02.502 --> 15:05.973
NO MOVIN'.
NO LEAVIN'.

15:06.006 --> 15:08.241
IT'S ALL RIGHT
THE WAY IT IS.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

15:08.275 --> 15:10.944
YOU WANNA TELL ME
IT'S ALL RIGHT, SETHE,

15:10.978 --> 15:12.980
AND THAT CHILD'S HALF
OUTTA HER MIND.

15:13.013 --> 15:14.847
[ Clattering ]

15:16.083 --> 15:19.619
[ Denver Whimpering ]
HUSH, I SAY !

15:20.520 --> 15:24.257
I GOT A TREE
ON MY BACK...

15:24.291 --> 15:26.226
AND A HAINT
IN MY HOUSE...

15:26.259 --> 15:29.162
AND NOTHIN' IN BETWEEN
BUT THE DAUGHTER
I'M HOLDIN' IN MY ARMS.

15:29.196 --> 15:32.399
NO LEAVIN'.
NO RUNNIN' FROM NOTHIN'.

15:32.432 --> 15:34.301
YOU HEAR ME ?
[ Mumbling ]

15:34.334 --> 15:39.106
I WILL NEVER RUN
FROM ANOTHER THING
ON THIS EARTH.

15:42.976 --> 15:44.611
COME ON.

15:44.644 --> 15:47.247
YOU CAN SIT DOWN
AND EAT,

15:47.280 --> 15:50.283
OR YOU CAN
LEAVE US BE.
[ Sobbing ]

16:15.175 --> 16:18.111
[ Grunts ]

16:18.145 --> 16:19.746
LORD.

16:30.390 --> 16:32.059
WHAT TREE, SETHE ?

16:36.263 --> 16:39.299
HUH ?

16:39.332 --> 16:42.269
I DON'T SEE NOTHIN'
GROWIN' ON YOUR BACK.

16:45.004 --> 16:47.374
IT'S THERE ALL THE SAME.

16:47.407 --> 16:48.741
CHOKECHERRY TREE.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.680
LEAVES, BRANCHES.

16:54.614 --> 16:58.051
THAT WAS 18 YEARS AGO.

16:58.085 --> 17:00.520
- HAPPENED THAT NIGHT.
- THAT NIGHT ?

17:00.553 --> 17:05.092
- [ Screaming ]
- TREE COULD HAVE CHERRIES
BY NOW FOR ALL I KNOW.

17:05.125 --> 17:07.294
I AIN'T FOLLOWIN' YOU,
SETHE.

17:08.560 --> 17:10.396
I HAD MILK, PAUL D.

17:10.430 --> 17:11.763
[ Chattering ]

17:11.798 --> 17:14.233
I HAD MILK, SEE ?

17:15.468 --> 17:18.338
I WAS PREGNANT WITH DENVER,

17:18.371 --> 17:21.174
BUT I HADN'T STOPPED NURSIN'
MY BABY GIRL...

17:21.208 --> 17:24.411
BEFORE I SENT HER
AND THE BOYS OFF.

17:24.444 --> 17:26.113
[ Crying ]

17:26.146 --> 17:29.816
ALL I KNEW WAS, I HAD TO
GET MILK TO MY BABY GIRL.

17:31.318 --> 17:33.786
I THOUGHT WE WAS TALKIN'
ABOUT A TREE.

17:33.820 --> 17:38.291
WE WAS ALL SUPPOSED TO MEET
IN THE CORNFIELD.
NONE OF YOU CAME.

17:38.325 --> 17:42.795
I HAD TO LEAVE MY CHILDREN,
GO BACK LOOKIN' FOR HALLE.

17:42.829 --> 17:44.797
THAT'S WHEN I SAW YOU
IN THE SHED.

17:44.831 --> 17:47.767
SIXO DEAD. SCHOOLTEACHER
DONE GONE AND BURNT HIM.

17:47.800 --> 17:49.902
PAUL A TOO.
THEY HANG HIM FROM A TREE.

17:49.936 --> 17:53.273
SAID YOU WERE GONNA RUN
NO MATTER WHAT.

17:53.306 --> 17:55.308
I DIDN'T THINK YOU WOULD
MAKE IT TO THE GATE.

17:55.342 --> 17:59.146
- I WENT BACK IN THE BARN
TO LOOK FOR HALLE.
- ANIMAL.

17:59.179 --> 18:01.314
THAT'S WHEN
SCHOOLTEACHER SAW ME.

18:01.348 --> 18:03.116
[ Schoolteacher ]
WHAT'S IT TASTE LIKE ?

18:03.150 --> 18:05.752
CAME IN THERE
WITH HIS BOYS AFTER ME.

18:05.785 --> 18:08.421
YOU'VE GOT
ANIMAL CHARACTERISTICS.

18:08.455 --> 18:10.957
THEM BOYS TOOK MY MILK.

18:10.990 --> 18:13.760
THAT'S MY BABY'S FOOD !

18:13.793 --> 18:16.663
THAT'S WHAT
THEY COME IN THERE FOR.

18:16.696 --> 18:19.599
[ Screaming ]

18:19.632 --> 18:23.436
HOLD ME DOWN,
TAKE IT.

18:24.604 --> 18:26.473
I TOLD MISS GARNER
ON 'EM.

18:26.506 --> 18:28.375
[ Sethe ]
THEY'RE LYIN', THE ANIMALS !

18:31.043 --> 18:33.846
SHE HAD THAT LUMP ON
HER NECK AND COULDN'T SPEAK.

18:33.880 --> 18:37.116
BUT HER EYES ROLLED OUT TEARS,
I REMEMBER.

18:39.319 --> 18:41.321
THEM BOYS FOUND OUT
I TOLD ON 'EM.

18:41.354 --> 18:46.159
[ Screaming ]
YOU'RE HORRIBLE
AND BEATEN UP !

18:46.193 --> 18:48.027
YOU'RE HORRIBLE
AND BEATEN UP !

18:48.060 --> 18:51.731
SCHOOLTEACHER HAD ONE OF 'EM
WHOOPIN' UP MY BACK.

18:52.965 --> 18:54.901
AND WHEN THEY CLOSED,

18:58.238 --> 19:00.072
IT LEFT A TREE.

19:04.977 --> 19:07.414
THEY USED COWHIDE
ON YOU.

19:14.086 --> 19:16.423
AND THEY TOOK MY MILK.

19:18.258 --> 19:21.093
THEY BEAT YOU
AND YOU WAS PREGNANT ?

19:23.330 --> 19:25.932
AND THEY TOOK MY MILK.

20:11.311 --> 20:14.146
OH, LORD, GIRL.

20:22.922 --> 20:26.493
[ Clattering,
Baby Crying ]

20:33.666 --> 20:36.168
[ Crying Continues ]

20:46.279 --> 20:47.947
[ Screaming ]

20:47.980 --> 20:50.817
[ Screaming ]
GODDAMN IT !

20:50.850 --> 20:53.653
HUSH UP !

20:53.686 --> 20:55.555
[ Barking ]

20:55.588 --> 20:58.291
[ Sethe ]
DENVER ! DENVER !

20:58.325 --> 20:59.992
MOVE ! MOVE !

21:00.026 --> 21:01.894
GET OUTTA THE WAY !

21:01.928 --> 21:04.931
[ Paul D ]
LEAVE THIS PLACE ALONE !

21:08.868 --> 21:11.838
I SAID, HUSH UP,
GODDAMN IT !

21:11.871 --> 21:14.607
PAUL D, LOOK OUT !

21:16.876 --> 21:18.678
PAUL D !

21:18.711 --> 21:21.548
[ Paul D Groaning ]

21:26.152 --> 21:30.957
- PAUL D !
- YOU WANNA FIGHT ?

21:30.990 --> 21:35.895
THEN COME ON, GODDAMN IT !
[ Yelling ]

21:39.799 --> 21:41.968
[ Panting ]

21:52.178 --> 21:54.981
[ Birds Twittering ]

22:05.992 --> 22:08.227
[ Panting Continues ]

22:31.451 --> 22:33.586
[ Coughing ]

25:03.269 --> 25:06.205
[ Chickens Clucking ]

25:25.024 --> 25:26.659
[ Baby Cooing ]

25:26.693 --> 25:29.696
[ Man ]
I WAS UP THERE IN THE LOFT !
[ Paul D Screaming ] HALLE !

25:29.729 --> 25:32.264
[ Sethe ]
THEM BOYS TOOK MY MILK.
HALLE !

25:32.298 --> 25:35.935
THAT'S WHAT
THEY COME IN THERE FOR.
[ Halle ] THE LOFT, THE LOFT.

25:35.968 --> 25:37.436
HALLE !
I SEEN IT ALL !

25:37.469 --> 25:42.274
[ Sethe ]
HOLD ME DOWN AND TAKE IT.
[ Screaming ]

25:42.308 --> 25:43.943
[ Gasping ]

25:43.976 --> 25:45.912
- HALLE !
- MILK IT LIKE A COW.

25:45.945 --> 25:50.149
- THAT'S WHAT WE MEAN
BY ANIMAL CHARACTERISTICS.
- HALLE ! STOP !

26:18.110 --> 26:20.880
[ Paul D ]
* LITTLE RICE

26:20.913 --> 26:22.915
* LITTLE BEAN

26:22.949 --> 26:27.553
* NO MEAT IN BETWEEN

26:27.586 --> 26:30.256
* HARD WORK AIN'T EASY

26:30.289 --> 26:32.324
[ Sethe ]
ANYBODY HERE ?

26:32.358 --> 26:35.628
MAMA !
MAMA !

26:35.662 --> 26:38.297
[ Chuckling ]

26:40.099 --> 26:43.069
SETHE ?
[ Clears Throat ]
HMM ?

26:43.102 --> 26:46.505
I WAS THINKIN'
OF LOOKIN' FOR WORK
AROUND HERE.

26:46.538 --> 26:50.009
WHAT YOU THINK ?
HMM. AIN'T MUCH.

26:50.042 --> 26:53.012
RIVER MOSTLY.
AND HOGS.

26:53.045 --> 26:55.014
WELL, I NEVER WORKED
ON THE RIVER,

26:55.047 --> 26:58.184
BUT I CAN PICK UP
ANYTHING HEAVY AS ME,
HOGS INCLUDED.

26:58.217 --> 27:01.688
WHITE FOLKS HERE
BETTER THAN KENTUCKY,

27:01.721 --> 27:04.190
BUT YOU JUST MIGHT
HAVE TO SCRAMBLE SOME.

27:04.223 --> 27:07.459
WELL, IT AIN'T
WHETHER I SCRAMBLE,
IT'S WHERE.

27:07.493 --> 27:10.930
YOU SAYIN'
IT'S ALL RIGHT
TO SCRAMBLE HERE ?

27:10.963 --> 27:14.266
BETTER THAN ALL RIGHT.

27:14.300 --> 27:18.705
YOUR GIRL, DENVER,
IT SEEMS SHE OF
A DIFFERENT MIND THOUGH.

27:18.738 --> 27:21.140
YOU DON'T NEVER HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT DENVER.

27:21.173 --> 27:25.144
SHE A CHARMED CHILD
FROM THE BEGINNING.

27:25.177 --> 27:28.047
GOTTA KNOW ONE THING
THOUGH, PAUL D.

27:28.080 --> 27:30.316
THIS HERE
AIN'T NO BETTER LIFE.

27:30.349 --> 27:32.184
JUST NOT THAT OTHER ONE.

27:32.218 --> 27:35.054
WHAT I DO HERE--
ALL I EVER DO...

27:35.087 --> 27:38.157
IS KEEP DENVER
FROM THAT OTHER ONE.

27:38.190 --> 27:41.961
WON'T LET THE PAST
IN MY YARD AGAIN.
YOU UNDERSTAND ?

27:41.994 --> 27:44.897
DANGEROUS TO LOVE
ANY ONE THING THAT MUCH,
SETHE.

27:44.931 --> 27:47.900
THE BEST THING
IS TO LOVE EVERYTHING
JUST A LITTLE BIT.

27:47.934 --> 27:52.538
THAT WAY,
IF IT BREAKS OR RUNS OFF
OR IS TAKEN AWAY,

27:52.571 --> 27:54.807
YOU KNOW, MAYBE,
YOU STILL HAVE
A LITTLE LOVE LEFT OVER.

27:54.841 --> 27:58.044
HMM. WELL, THAT'S THE WAY
IT IS, PAUL D.

27:58.077 --> 28:03.049
IF I HAVE TO CHOOSE,
WELL, AIN'T NO CHOICE.

28:03.082 --> 28:05.918
THAT'S THE WHOLE POINT.
I AIN'T ASKIN' YOU
TO CHOOSE.

28:05.952 --> 28:09.688
I JUST WANNA KNOW
IF THERE'S A PLACE
FOR ME.

28:09.722 --> 28:13.525
IF THERE'S MORE THAN,
"YOU CAN STAY, IT'S FINE."

28:13.559 --> 28:17.764
MORE LIKE,
"I WANT YOU HERE, PAUL."

28:17.797 --> 28:22.234
MAYBE WE OUGHT
TO JUST LEAVE THINGS
THE WAY THEY ARE.

28:22.268 --> 28:26.705
SETHE, I'M NOT SAYIN' THIS
'CAUSE I NEED A PLACE TO STAY.

28:26.739 --> 28:30.843
WE COULD MAKE A LIFE, GIRL.
A LIFE.

28:30.877 --> 28:34.613
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT,
PAUL D GARNER.
LEAVE IT TO ME !

28:34.646 --> 28:38.284
SEE HOW IT GOES.
NO PROMISES IF YOU DON'T
WANNA MAKE NONE.

28:38.317 --> 28:41.187
JUST LEAVE IT TO ME.
ALL RIGHT ?

28:41.220 --> 28:43.122
[ Hoofbeats Clattering ]

28:43.155 --> 28:46.893
ALL RIGHT,
WE'LL SEE HOW IT GOES.
[ Sighing ]

28:46.926 --> 28:50.763
YOU'RE WILLIN'
TO LEAVE IT TO ME ?

28:50.797 --> 28:52.899
SOME OF IT.

28:52.932 --> 28:56.969
SOME.
OKAY. OKAY.

28:57.003 --> 28:59.972
HERE'S SOME.
THERE'S A CARNIVAL IN TOWN.

29:00.006 --> 29:02.741
THURSDAYS FOR COLOREDS,
AND I GOT TWO DOLLARS.

29:02.775 --> 29:05.744
ME, YOU AND DENVER
GONNA SPEND EVERY PENNY.

29:05.778 --> 29:08.915
WHAT YOU SAY ?
I DON'T KNOW.

29:08.948 --> 29:11.083
ALL RIGHT ?

29:14.586 --> 29:17.356
NO.
AW--
PLEASE !

29:23.029 --> 29:27.099
[ Denver ]
YOU THINK BABY GHOST'S
REALLY GONE ?

29:29.035 --> 29:30.769
DON'T KNOW.

29:32.104 --> 29:34.941
SHE MY SISTER.

29:34.974 --> 29:36.708
I MISS HER.

29:38.644 --> 29:44.083
[ Paul D ]
* WELL, I SAID
COME HERE, BLACK WOMAN *

29:44.116 --> 29:46.752
I WISH HE'D SHUT UP.
HE GONNA RUIN EVERYTHING.

29:46.785 --> 29:51.023
SHH.
GIVE HIM A CHANCE.
* [ Singing Continues ]

29:51.057 --> 29:53.659
DO THAT
FOR ME.
WHY ?

29:53.692 --> 29:55.828
HOW LONG
HE STAYIN' ?

29:57.296 --> 30:02.701
DON'T KNOW.
* I SAID
RUN HERE, BLACK WOMAN *

30:02.734 --> 30:07.106
I THINK THE BABY
AIN'T GONE.

30:07.139 --> 30:09.909
I THINK THE BABY
GOT PLANS.

30:12.879 --> 30:15.481
MAYBE.
* I KNOW YOUR HOUSE

30:16.382 --> 30:18.717
[ Sethe ]
MAYBE SO.

30:22.989 --> 30:26.392
[ Bird Squawking,
Wings Fluttering ]

30:26.425 --> 30:30.329
[ Snoring ]

30:30.362 --> 30:32.698
[ Wheezing ]

30:37.870 --> 30:43.109
[ Snoring, Wheezing
Continue ]

30:46.112 --> 30:48.447
[ Gasping ]

31:09.135 --> 31:11.470
[ Wheezing Continues ]

31:17.543 --> 31:21.147
[ Snoring ]

31:41.300 --> 31:44.636
[ Wheezing, Snorting ]

31:53.779 --> 31:58.784
* [ Calliope ]
[ Man ] COME ONE, COME FORWARD,
COME ALL ! DO NOT FEAR !

31:58.817 --> 32:03.789
COME INSIDE TO THE LARGEST LADY,
ROUNDELLA, WITH ME TODAY.

32:03.822 --> 32:08.160
SWEET, GENTLE AND DELICATE,
EATING A CHICKEN FROM EACH HAND.

32:08.194 --> 32:13.299
COME INSIDE NOW AND SEE HER.
DON'T BE AFRAID. COME THIS WAY.
WAIT ! COME BACK !

32:13.332 --> 32:15.301
[ Crowd Chattering ]

32:19.171 --> 32:21.840
...AND WHO WILL SWALLOW
A CONFEDERATE SWORD
TO THE HILT

32:21.873 --> 32:24.076
IN FRONT OF
YOUR VERY EYES.

32:24.110 --> 32:27.479
STEP FORWARD AND SEE !
WHOO !

32:27.513 --> 32:30.582
[ Chattering ]

32:30.616 --> 32:32.518
OH, GRACE.

32:32.551 --> 32:36.522
YOU'LL NEVER BELIEVE
WHO COME WALKIN' UP IN HERE.
[ Lion Growling ]

32:36.555 --> 32:39.858
HOW DO ?
[ Man ]
COME ON, LUCY.

32:39.891 --> 32:42.828
[ Boy ]
DON'T FORGET
THE PIG RIDE.

32:42.861 --> 32:45.031
[ Paul D ]
HOW DO, MA'AM ?

32:45.064 --> 32:49.035
[ Crowd Gasping,
Applauding ]

32:49.068 --> 32:52.704
STEP INSIDE TO SEE
THE THINGS YOU THOUGHT
COULD NEVER BE.

32:52.738 --> 32:56.208
THE FEROCIOUS AFRICAN SAVAGE,
CLUCK BUTOO !

32:56.242 --> 33:01.013
BORN WITH FANGS,
RAISED BY WILD ANIMALS
AND CAPTURED CRAZY.

33:06.685 --> 33:09.188
LOOK HOW FAT
SHE IS, MAMA.

33:09.221 --> 33:11.257
[ Growling ]

33:15.061 --> 33:17.729
I-I KNEW THIS ONE
BACK IN ROANOKE.

33:21.067 --> 33:25.137
WANT SOME LICORICE,
DENVER ?
YES, PLEASE.

33:25.171 --> 33:27.573
PEPPERMINT STICK ?
YES, PLEASE.

33:27.606 --> 33:31.677
- SOME GUMDROPS ?
- YES, PLEASE.

33:34.280 --> 33:36.382
MIND IF I TAKE A SIP ?

33:46.792 --> 33:50.396
MMM.
MMM !

33:54.300 --> 33:57.103
HEY, DENVER !

33:57.136 --> 33:59.738
HI.

33:59.771 --> 34:02.274
THANK YOU.

34:05.811 --> 34:08.746
I'LL TAKE
ONE OF THOSE LEMONADES TOO.

34:13.918 --> 34:15.621
BUT TELL ME
ABOUT SOME WORK.

34:15.654 --> 34:19.358
I MEAN, TELL ME ABOUT
WHERE I CAN FIND SOME.
WELL, THEY HAVE--

34:19.391 --> 34:22.694
[ Man ]
...TURNS HIS HEAD
INSIDE HIS OWN FACE

34:22.728 --> 34:26.632
AND PULLS HIS EARS--
[ Men Chattering ]

34:26.665 --> 34:30.136
[ Crowd Singing ]
* HEADIN' BACK

34:30.168 --> 34:33.772
* GOIN' HOME

34:33.804 --> 34:37.074
* [ Continues ]

34:37.109 --> 34:40.411
[ Chattering ]

34:40.446 --> 34:42.214
WHAT'S THAT ?

34:42.248 --> 34:46.152
* AIN'T WANNA
HURT NOBODY *

34:46.185 --> 34:49.487
* OH, NO
[ Snoring ]

34:49.521 --> 34:52.090
* AIN'T GONNA
HURT NOBODY *

34:52.123 --> 34:56.328
* OH, LORD

34:56.362 --> 34:58.430
* [ Continues ]

34:58.464 --> 35:02.368
[ Gasping ]

35:14.513 --> 35:16.715
EXCUSE ME.

35:50.216 --> 35:52.017
[ Coughing ]

35:52.050 --> 35:55.020
YOU FROM
AROUND HERE ?

36:10.902 --> 36:13.038
WHAT MIGHT
YOUR NAME BE ?

36:13.071 --> 36:17.476
[ Speaking In
Guttural Voice ]
B...

36:17.509 --> 36:20.178
E...

36:20.212 --> 36:22.548
L...

36:22.581 --> 36:24.182
O...

36:24.216 --> 36:26.585
V...

36:26.618 --> 36:29.655
E...

36:29.688 --> 36:32.090
D.

36:32.123 --> 36:36.027
BELOVED.
[ Grunting ]

36:37.296 --> 36:40.031
THAT'S A PRETTY NAME,
BELOVED.

36:40.065 --> 36:43.769
WHY DON'T YOU REST YOURSELF
WHILE I-- I FIX US A LITTLE
SOMETHIN'.

36:43.802 --> 36:48.607
WE JUST GOT BACK
FROM THE CARNIVAL
OVER IN CINCINNATI.

36:48.640 --> 36:52.678
[ Paul D ]
MISS ? MISS ?

36:52.711 --> 36:55.314
YOU WANNA REST A SPELL ?

37:02.321 --> 37:04.423
- [ Beloved Gasping ]
- I GOT HER !

37:04.456 --> 37:07.092
I GOT HER.
I GOT HER.

37:10.296 --> 37:12.464
[ Whimpering ]

37:25.577 --> 37:27.946
LOOK AT HER FEET.

37:27.979 --> 37:30.516
AIN'T WALKIN' FEET.

37:31.950 --> 37:33.752
MORE LIKE SHE...
[ Wheezing ]

37:33.785 --> 37:36.154
RIDE FROM SOMEWHERE
ALL THE WAY HERE.

37:36.187 --> 37:38.924
IS SHE FEVERISH, DENVER ?

37:40.359 --> 37:41.793
NO, SHE COLD.

37:41.827 --> 37:46.432
[ Paul D ]
COULD HAVE THE CHOLERA.
SHE AIN'T SICK.

38:01.179 --> 38:05.451
[ Paul D Chuckling ]
[ Sethe ] NAH, IT'S JUST
A LITTLE SOMETHIN' I WHIPPED UP.

38:05.484 --> 38:08.186
A LITTLE SOMETHIN'
YOU WHIPPED UP ?

38:08.219 --> 38:11.022
MMM. MMM.
[ Beloved Moaning ]

38:14.225 --> 38:16.662
HEARD THERE'S WORK
DOWN IN BUCKTOWN.

38:17.796 --> 38:20.499
GO SEE IT
FOR MYSELF TODAY.

38:26.805 --> 38:29.408
[ Paul D And Sethe
Laughing ]

38:39.351 --> 38:41.487
[ Wheezing ]

38:44.756 --> 38:48.594
[ Snoring ]

38:56.868 --> 38:59.037
MMM-MM.

38:59.070 --> 39:03.542
[ Paul D ]
WHOA ! WHOA !
HEY ! HO-HO ! WHOA !

39:03.575 --> 39:05.377
HEY !

39:05.411 --> 39:07.546
[ Chattering ]

39:10.281 --> 39:13.251
[ Wheezing, Snoring
Continue ]

39:39.911 --> 39:43.314
* [ Denver Singing ]

39:47.285 --> 39:50.388
* [ Stops ]
[ Wheezing, Snoring
Continue ]

40:06.505 --> 40:08.674
[ Grunting ]

40:25.190 --> 40:27.693
YOU WANNA TRY SOME ?

40:43.942 --> 40:47.178
COME ON, COME ON.
COME ON.

40:47.212 --> 40:50.516
OVER HERE.
COME ON.
[ Beloved Whee ]

40:50.549 --> 40:52.718
THERE YOU GO.

40:57.823 --> 41:00.025
COME ON !
[ Laughing ]

41:00.058 --> 41:05.230
I KNEW YOU COULD DO IT.
[ Chuckling ]
OH.

41:12.571 --> 41:14.740
YOU HUNGRY ?

41:18.243 --> 41:20.411
[ Giggles ]

41:31.757 --> 41:34.425
IT'S GOOD !

41:38.096 --> 41:40.365
[ Giggling ]

41:44.102 --> 41:46.371
SLOW DOWN.

42:03.589 --> 42:05.090
[ Laughing ]

42:05.123 --> 42:08.293
* [ Woman Vocalizing ]

42:22.240 --> 42:24.442
COME ON.

42:28.246 --> 42:31.282
CHICKEN, CHICKEN,
SHOO, SHOO, SHOO.

42:31.316 --> 42:36.955
* [ Vocalizing Stops ]
I CALL THIS ONE JUNE,

42:36.988 --> 42:39.290
AND THAT'S MAY.

42:40.759 --> 42:43.128
YOU GOTTA DO SOFT TOUCH.

42:43.161 --> 42:46.297
REMEMBER ?
CAN YOU DO SOFT TOUCH ?

42:46.331 --> 42:48.634
TOUCH IT--
NO !

42:48.667 --> 42:50.836
BELOVED.

44:25.030 --> 44:27.565
[ Wheezing ]

44:27.598 --> 44:29.600
BELOVED.

44:31.069 --> 44:34.572
I HELP
MAKE YOU BREAD.

44:36.041 --> 44:37.909
THAT'S NICE.

44:37.943 --> 44:40.979
IS MY APRON HERE ?

44:41.012 --> 44:43.181
ALL RIGHT,
WE NEED A LITTLE FLOUR.
WE NEED SOME--

44:43.214 --> 44:46.084
I DON'T KNOW. I SEE
YOU GOT ALL MY THINGS
LAID OUT.

44:46.117 --> 44:50.255
OH, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT. NOW YOU NEED
SOME OF THAT RIGHT THERE.

44:50.288 --> 44:52.423
YOU NEED THIS.

44:52.457 --> 44:54.893
THERE.
WAIT, WAIT.

44:54.926 --> 44:58.897
[ Paul D ]
* LITTLE RICE, LITTLE BEAN

44:58.930 --> 45:01.432
* AIN'T NO MEAT
IN BETWEEN *

45:01.466 --> 45:03.234
[ Beloved Chattering ]

45:03.268 --> 45:08.774
[ Denver Laughing ]
OOH, LOOK AT YOU.

45:08.807 --> 45:12.010
OKAY, PUT IT DOWN.
PUT IT BACK.

45:12.043 --> 45:13.745
* [ Continues ]

45:13.779 --> 45:17.682
[ Beloved ]
GO INSIDE AND GET BISCUIT.

45:17.715 --> 45:19.617
EASY.

45:19.650 --> 45:23.088
[ Denver ]
* I WENT DOWNTOWN
TO GET MY GRITS *

45:23.121 --> 45:26.424
* CAME BACK HOME
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF *

45:26.457 --> 45:28.894
* JUST A-PULLIN'
THE SKIFF *

45:28.927 --> 45:32.030
* I RAN UPSTAIRS
TO MAKE MY BED *

45:32.063 --> 45:35.066
* I MADE A MISTAKE
AND I BUMPED MY HEAD *

45:35.100 --> 45:38.636
* JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF *

45:38.669 --> 45:42.073
* WENT DOWNSTAIRS
TO MILK MY COW *

45:42.107 --> 45:44.810
* I MADE A MISTAKE
AND I MILKED MY SOW *

45:44.843 --> 45:48.146
* JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF *

45:48.179 --> 45:51.649
* TOMORROW, TOMORROW
TOMORROW NEVER COMES *

45:51.682 --> 45:55.153
* TOMORROW, TOMORROW
TOMORROW NEVER COMES *

45:55.186 --> 45:58.689
* [ Singing ]

46:19.110 --> 46:22.513
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

46:24.382 --> 46:27.318
[ Beloved
Whimpering ]
COME ON !

46:27.352 --> 46:29.154
CLOUDS LOOK LIKE
THEY'RE GONNA BURST.

46:29.187 --> 46:31.823
[ All Screaming,
Laughing ]
OH, HERE IT COME !

46:31.857 --> 46:33.324
HERE, HERE !
COME ON, GIRL.

46:33.358 --> 46:36.027
HERE, MAMA !
PULL !
PULL IT !

46:36.061 --> 46:37.863
GO ! GO !
HURRY UP !
HURRY UP. COME ON.

46:37.896 --> 46:40.265
BELOVED,
PICK UP THAT SHEET.
RUN ! IT'S RAINING !

46:40.298 --> 46:42.868
YOU'RE DRAGGIN' IT
ON THE GROUND.
GO !

46:42.901 --> 46:45.703
[ Screaming, Laughing
Continue ]

46:49.240 --> 46:52.377
STOP DRAGGIN' THEM SHEETS.
PICK 'EM UP OFF THE GROUND NOW,

46:52.410 --> 46:55.046
SO WE DON'T HAVE TO
WASH 'EM AGAIN.

46:55.080 --> 46:57.282
COME ON. WHOO !

46:57.315 --> 47:00.018
ALMOST DIDN'T MAKE IT.

47:00.051 --> 47:02.620
SPREAD 'EM OUT.
BELOVED, PUT THAT SHEET
DOWN NOW.

47:02.653 --> 47:05.156
SPREAD IT OUT.
KEEP IT UP
OFF THE FLOOR.

47:06.424 --> 47:08.593
* [ Singing ]

47:53.071 --> 47:55.073
WHERE...

47:55.106 --> 47:58.209
YOUR DIAMONDS ?

47:59.577 --> 48:02.180
DIAMONDS ?
[ Chuckles ]

48:02.213 --> 48:05.250
WHAT WOULD I BE DOIN'
WITH DIAMONDS ?

48:05.283 --> 48:08.786
ON YOUR EARS.

48:11.489 --> 48:13.658
WISH I DID.

48:14.592 --> 48:18.129
COME TO THINK OF IT,

48:18.163 --> 48:21.132
I HAD SOME CRYSTAL ONCE.

48:21.166 --> 48:24.102
PRESENT FROM THE LADY
I USED TO WORK FOR.

48:24.135 --> 48:26.271
TELL ME.

48:27.905 --> 48:30.741
TELL ME
YOUR DIAMONDS.

48:30.775 --> 48:33.544
WEDDING PRESENT
FROM MISS GARNER...

48:33.578 --> 48:35.646
BACK AT SWEET HOME...

48:35.680 --> 48:41.052
WHEN HALLE AND ME GOT MARRIED--
WHAT THEY CALLED MARRIED
BACK THERE AND THEN.

48:41.086 --> 48:44.822
GUESS SHE SAW HOW BAD
I FELT WHEN...

48:44.855 --> 48:48.994
I SAW THERE WASN'T GONNA BE
NO CEREMONY, NO PREACHER.

48:49.027 --> 48:53.398
I NEVER SAW YOU
WITH NO CRYSTALS.

48:53.431 --> 48:56.101
GONE.

48:56.134 --> 48:58.169
LONG GONE.

49:01.706 --> 49:05.010
COME HERE, GIRL.
YOU BEST UNBRAID
THAT HAIR.

49:06.211 --> 49:08.313
COME ON.
GET THE COMB.

49:10.648 --> 49:12.683
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

49:14.152 --> 49:16.021
OW !
THAT HURTS.

49:16.054 --> 49:19.524
COMB IT EVERY DAY,
IT WON'T.

49:19.557 --> 49:21.826
YOUR WOMAN...

49:21.859 --> 49:25.330
NEVER FIX UP
YOUR HAIR ?

49:26.531 --> 49:29.000
MY WOMAN ?
YOU MEAN MY MOTHER ?

49:29.034 --> 49:32.170
MAMA DON'T TALK ABOUT
ALL THOSE THINGS.

49:32.203 --> 49:34.572
TELL ME.

49:37.975 --> 49:39.944
IF SHE DID,
I DON'T REMEMBER.

49:39.977 --> 49:44.215
I DON'T THINK I SAW HER
BUT A FEW TIMES
OUT IN THE FIELD...

49:44.249 --> 49:47.718
ONCE WORKIN' INDIGO.

49:47.752 --> 49:53.058
BY THE TIME
I WOKE UP MORNINGS,
SHE WAS IN LINE.

49:53.091 --> 49:56.994
HMM. IF THE MOON WAS BRIGHT,
THEY WORKED BY ITS LIGHT.

49:57.028 --> 50:00.765
SUNDAYS, SHE SLEPT
LIKE A STICK.

50:03.234 --> 50:06.671
TELL ME ABOUT HER.

50:09.006 --> 50:13.010
I REMEMBER, ONCE,
SHE PICKED ME UP

50:13.044 --> 50:15.646
AND CARRIED ME
BEHIND THE SMOKEHOUSE.

50:15.680 --> 50:18.616
ONLY THING I DO REMEMBER,
IN FACT.

50:20.385 --> 50:26.057
SHE OPENED UP HER DRESS,
AND RIGHT ON HER RIB--

50:26.091 --> 50:28.126
RIGHT HERE--

50:31.096 --> 50:33.030
WAS A CIRCLE...

50:33.064 --> 50:37.001
AND A CROSS
BURNT RIGHT IN THE SKIN.

50:37.034 --> 50:40.438
SHE POINTS AT THIS MARK,
AND SHE SAYS--

50:40.471 --> 50:42.607
SHE SAYS TO ME,

50:42.640 --> 50:48.213
"THIS IS YOUR MA'AM.
I'M THE ONLY ONE
GOT THIS MARK NOW.

50:48.246 --> 50:50.047
"THE REST ALL DEAD.

50:50.081 --> 50:53.351
"SOMETHIN' HAPPEN TO ME,
YOU CAN'T TELL ME
BY MY FACE,

50:53.384 --> 50:56.421
YOU KNOW ME
BY THIS MARK."

50:56.454 --> 50:58.523
SCARED ME
SO I COULDN'T THINK
OF NOTHIN' TO SAY,

50:58.556 --> 51:01.726
SO I SAYS, "YES, MA'AM.

51:01.759 --> 51:04.762
"BUT HOW YOU KNOW ME ?
MARK THE MARK ON ME.

51:04.795 --> 51:07.132
MARK ME TOO."

51:07.165 --> 51:09.467
DID SHE ?

51:09.500 --> 51:11.302
NO.

51:11.336 --> 51:14.405
SHE SLAPPED MY FACE.

51:17.975 --> 51:20.678
I DIDN'T UNDERSTAND IT THEN.

51:22.513 --> 51:25.850
NOT TILL I HAD
A MARK OF MY OWN.

51:26.851 --> 51:32.157
[ Beloved ]
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER ?

51:32.190 --> 51:35.160
HUNG.

51:38.363 --> 51:43.301
MA'AM.
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU, MA'AM ?

51:46.103 --> 51:48.206
WHY THEY HANG
YOUR MAMA ?

51:49.874 --> 51:53.010
I NEVER FOUND OUT.

51:54.345 --> 51:56.181
WAS A LOT OF 'EM.

51:56.214 --> 51:58.115
[ People Crying ]

51:58.149 --> 52:01.219
[ Bones Cracking ]
[ Woman Sobbing ]

52:47.164 --> 52:50.535
PAUL D BE HERE
IN A MINUTE.

52:55.072 --> 52:56.374
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

53:00.110 --> 53:03.013
HOPE THIS PUDDING'S
GOOD TONIGHT.

53:05.216 --> 53:08.286
DENVER, PASS ME
YOUR PLATE DOWN HERE.

53:12.122 --> 53:14.292
PAUL D.

53:36.146 --> 53:39.917
WHERE YOU BEEN
ALL THEM YEARS...

53:39.950 --> 53:43.254
SINCE SWEET HOME,
MR. PAUL ?

53:43.288 --> 53:46.123
AIN'T YOU GOT
NO PEOPLE ?

53:46.156 --> 53:49.494
YOU WANNA KNOW
ABOUT ME NOW.
UH-HUH.

53:56.767 --> 53:59.003
I GOT NO PEOPLE.

54:04.275 --> 54:06.243
EIGHTEEN YEARS SINCE
I LEFT SWEET HOME,

54:06.277 --> 54:08.479
AND I'VE BEEN
WALKIN' THE WHOLE TIME.

54:08.513 --> 54:13.984
MOVE, WALK, RUN, HIDE,
SOMETIMES STEAL AND MOVE ON.

54:15.620 --> 54:19.290
ONLY TIME I STAYED IN ONE SPOT
FOR MORE THAN A MONTH OR SO...

54:19.324 --> 54:22.293
WAS WITH A WEAVER WOMAN
IN WILMINGTON, DELAWARE.

54:22.327 --> 54:24.929
MEANEST PLACE FOR A NEGRO
I EVER SEEN...

54:24.962 --> 54:27.965
OUTSIDE OF PULASKI COUNTY,
KENTUCKY.

54:27.998 --> 54:32.269
I SEEN NEGROES
SO STUNNED AND HUNGRY,

54:32.303 --> 54:35.272
THEY LIVED IN CAVES,
FOUGHT OWLS FOR FOOD.

54:35.306 --> 54:37.842
SEEN SOME WHO SLEPT
IN TREES IN THE DAY...

54:37.875 --> 54:39.510
AND MOVED ONLY BY NIGHT,

54:39.544 --> 54:43.180
WHO BURIED THEMSELVES IN SLOP
TO HIDE FROM...

54:43.213 --> 54:47.017
POSSES AND LAWMEN
AND REGULATORS.

54:47.051 --> 54:49.754
MET A NEGRO BOY ONCE--
ABOUT 14--

54:49.787 --> 54:52.523
WHO LIVED BY HISSELF
IN THE WOODS...
[ Sighing ]

54:52.557 --> 54:56.327
AND SAID HE COULD NEVER REMEMBER
LIVIN' ANYWHERE ELSE.

54:56.361 --> 55:00.130
SEEN A WITLESS
COLORED WOMAN HANG...

55:00.164 --> 55:03.568
FOR STEALING DUCKS
SHE BELIEVED WAS HER OWN BABIES.

55:07.805 --> 55:10.975
IN ALL THESE YEARS,
GIRL,

55:11.008 --> 55:13.544
YOU BEAT ALL.

55:13.578 --> 55:16.313
I AIN'T NEVER SEEN
A NEGRO LIKE YOU.

55:19.049 --> 55:22.887
I THINK IT'S TIME
YOU TELL US A LITTLE SOMETHIN'
ABOUT YOURSELF.

55:22.920 --> 55:24.622
SHE DON'T
REMEMBER NOTHIN'.

55:24.655 --> 55:27.324
OH, YOU'D BE SURPRISED
WHAT YOU START REMEMBERIN'

55:27.358 --> 55:29.427
SOON AS YOU START TALKIN'.

55:31.596 --> 55:35.099
AIN'T YOU GOT
NO BROTHERS OR SISTERS ?

55:39.269 --> 55:43.073
I AIN'T GOT NOBODY.

55:43.107 --> 55:45.410
PAUL D, STOP IT.

55:46.511 --> 55:49.747
DENVER, HELP ME
CLEAN UP THIS TABLE.

55:49.780 --> 55:51.616
I WANNA KNOW, SETHE.

55:55.119 --> 55:58.956
WHAT YOU LOOKIN' FOR
WHEN YOU COME HERE, BELOVED ?

56:00.891 --> 56:03.027
THIS PLACE.

56:05.129 --> 56:08.599
I LOOK FOR THIS PLACE
I COULD BE IN.

56:08.633 --> 56:11.469
SOMEBODY TELL YOU
ABOUT THIS PLACE ?

56:17.775 --> 56:20.511
SHE TOLD ME.

56:20.545 --> 56:25.950
WHEN I WAS AT THE BRIDGE,
SHE TOLD ME.

56:25.983 --> 56:29.319
HOW YOU COME ?
WHO BRUNG YA ?

56:31.055 --> 56:33.424
I WALK HERE.

56:35.993 --> 56:41.532
IT'S A LONG, LONG,
LONG, LONG WAY.

56:41.566 --> 56:45.470
NOBODY BRING ME.
YOU WEARIN'
NEW SHOES, GAL.

56:45.503 --> 56:49.073
IF YOU WALKED SO LONG, HOW COME
YOUR SHOES DON'T SHOW IT ?
[ Sethe ] PAUL D.

56:49.106 --> 56:51.041
STOP PICKIN' ON HER.

56:51.075 --> 56:52.577
I WANNA KNOW !

56:52.610 --> 56:54.645
WHERE YOU GET THEM SHOES
AND THE DRESS YOU HAD ON ?

56:54.679 --> 56:59.116
I TAKE THE SHOES,
AND I TAKE THE DRESS !

57:00.184 --> 57:03.988
THE SHOESTRINGS
DON'T FIT.

57:04.021 --> 57:07.191
I'LL TEACH YOU
HOW TO TIE YOUR SHOES.

57:09.460 --> 57:11.629
[ Gagging ]

57:15.032 --> 57:18.035
BELOVED. BELOVED !

57:19.103 --> 57:20.838
[ Coughing ]
BELOVED.

57:20.871 --> 57:23.340
BELOVED, BELOVED,
YOU ALL RIGHT ?

57:23.373 --> 57:25.142
LET IT OUT.
[ Hand Hitting Back ]

57:25.175 --> 57:27.845
GO TO SLEEP NOW.

57:27.878 --> 57:30.314
[ Denver ]
YOU CAN COME IN MY ROOM.

57:30.347 --> 57:33.217
I CAN TAKE CARE OF YOU
UP THERE.

57:35.686 --> 57:38.155
[ Crying Continues ]

57:42.993 --> 57:47.031
WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU ?
WHAT IS IT ABOUT HER
VEX YOU SO ?

57:47.064 --> 57:49.534
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT THE HOLD IS.

57:49.567 --> 57:53.704
IT'S CLEAR WHY SHE HOLD
ON TO YOU. I JUST CAN'T SEE
WHY YOU HOLDIN' ON TO HER.

57:53.738 --> 57:56.607
WHAT YOU CARE
WHO HOLDIN' ON TO WHO ?

57:56.641 --> 57:59.043
SHE NICE GIRL,
COMPANY FOR DENVER.

57:59.076 --> 58:01.211
THERE'S SOMETHING FUNNY
ABOUT THAT GAL.

58:01.245 --> 58:03.648
ACT SICK, SOUND SICK,
BUT SHE DON'T LOOK SICK.

58:03.681 --> 58:06.383
EATS SWEETS ALL DAY LONG,
AS STRONG AS A BULL.

58:06.416 --> 58:10.788
SHE NOT STRONG. SHE CAN'T
HARDLY EVEN WALK WITHOUT
HOLDIN' ON TO SOMETHIN'.

58:10.821 --> 58:13.558
CAN'T WALK,
BUT I SEEN HER PICK UP
THE ROCKER WITH ONE HAND.

58:13.591 --> 58:15.626
YOU AIN'T SEEN
NO SUCH A-THING.

58:15.660 --> 58:19.163
HEY, DON'T TELL ME.
ASK DENVER.
SHE RIGHT THERE WITH HER.

58:20.330 --> 58:24.368
SETHE, SETHE, BABY.

58:24.401 --> 58:29.239
WE WERE STARTIN' TO FEEL
A LITTLE LIKE A FAMILY OURSELF
TILL SHE COME ALONG.

58:29.273 --> 58:33.343
IS THAT WHAT GOT
YOUR TEETH ON EDGE ?
IT'S A FEELIN' IN ME.

58:33.377 --> 58:37.748
I CAN'T PLACE IT.
IT'S HER.
YOU WANNA
FEEL SOMETHIN' ?

58:37.782 --> 58:41.586
FEEL WHAT IT FEEL LIKE
TO BE A COLORED WOMAN
ROAMIN' THE ROADS.

58:41.619 --> 58:44.922
AND ANYTHING GOD MADE
LIABLE TO JUMP ON YOU.
FEEL THAT !

58:44.955 --> 58:46.824
I KNOW EVERY BIT
OF THAT, SETHE.

58:46.857 --> 58:49.594
I WASN'T BORN YESTERDAY,
AND I NEVER MISTREATED A WOMAN
IN MY LIFE.

58:49.627 --> 58:52.597
WELL, THAT MAKES
ONE OF YOU
IN THIS WORLD.

58:52.630 --> 58:55.299
ONE. NOT TWO ?

58:58.969 --> 59:01.205
NO, NOT TWO.

59:02.807 --> 59:05.943
WHAT'D HALLE
EVER DO TO YOU ?
HALLE STOOD BY YOU.

59:05.976 --> 59:08.779
HALLE RAN OFF.

59:08.813 --> 59:12.249
HE LEFT ME,
AND HE LEFT
OUR CHILDREN.

59:12.282 --> 59:15.285
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.
WHO HE LEAVE THEN
IF HE DIDN'T LEAVE ME ?

59:15.319 --> 59:18.756
HE WASN'T THERE.
HE WASN'T WHERE HE SAID
HE WAS GONNA BE.

59:18.789 --> 59:21.626
I HAD TO PACK MY BABIES OFF
AHEAD OF ME ON THEIR OWN.

59:21.659 --> 59:23.628
STAYED BEHIND
TO LOOK FOR HIM.

59:23.661 --> 59:27.264
GOT CAUGHT BY SCHOOLTEACHER
AND HIS BOYS FOR MY TROUBLE.

59:27.297 --> 59:29.600
[ Dishes Clattering ]

59:33.671 --> 59:37.407
HE COULDN'T GET OUT
THE... LOFT, I EXPECT.

59:40.611 --> 59:42.312
LOFT ?

59:42.346 --> 59:44.581
WHAT LOFT ?

59:44.615 --> 59:47.417
ONE IN THE BARN,
I RECKON.

59:52.356 --> 59:54.859
HE WAS THERE ?

59:56.794 --> 59:59.296
HOW DO YOU KNOW ?

01:00:01.799 --> 01:00:03.834
MORNIN' AFTER YOU RUN,
I SEEN HALLE...

01:00:03.868 --> 01:00:06.671
CHAINED TO A POST.

01:00:06.704 --> 01:00:10.074
I SAID, "WHAT HAPPENED ?
WHERE YOU BEEN ?"

01:00:10.107 --> 01:00:14.178
"THE LOFT, THE LOFT.
THE LOFT."

01:00:14.211 --> 01:00:15.946
THAT'S ALL HE SAID.

01:00:15.980 --> 01:00:20.885
COULD NEVER FIGURE OUT
WHAT HE MEANT BY THAT.
[ Sighing ]

01:00:24.388 --> 01:00:28.693
HE SAW THEM BOYS
DO THAT TO ME ?

01:00:28.726 --> 01:00:31.996
AND HE LET THEM
KEEP ON BREATHIN' ?

01:00:32.029 --> 01:00:34.765
I-I ASK HIM,

01:00:34.799 --> 01:00:36.934
"HOW COME YOU DIDN'T RUN
WITH SETHE ?"

01:00:36.967 --> 01:00:38.803
HE NEVER ANSWERED ME.

01:00:38.836 --> 01:00:40.671
I SEEN HIM ONCE MORE,

01:00:40.705 --> 01:00:43.373
THE DAY SCHOOLTEACHER
SOLD ME TO BRANDYWINE.

01:00:43.407 --> 01:00:46.343
TAKIN' ME AWAY
IN THE WAGON.

01:00:46.376 --> 01:00:49.213
THERE HALLE WAS,
IN THE YARD,

01:00:49.246 --> 01:00:51.481
SITTIN' BY THE CHURN.

01:00:53.550 --> 01:00:57.187
THEY DIDN'T NEED TO PUT
NO CHAINS ON HIM NO MORE.

01:00:57.221 --> 01:00:59.523
HIS MIND WAS GONE.

01:01:07.264 --> 01:01:09.266
SETHE,

01:01:13.738 --> 01:01:17.307
A MAN AIN'T
A GODDAMN AX,

01:01:17.341 --> 01:01:19.476
CHOPPIN' AND HACKIN',

01:01:19.509 --> 01:01:22.880
BUSTIN' EVERY MINUTE
OF THE DAY.

01:01:22.913 --> 01:01:24.849
THINGS GET TO HIM.

01:01:24.882 --> 01:01:29.686
THINGS HE CAN'T CHOP DOWN
'CAUSE THEY INSIDE.

01:01:29.720 --> 01:01:33.357
HALLE NEVER JUST RUN OFF
AND LEAVE YOU, SETHE.

01:01:34.258 --> 01:01:36.761
YOU SEE,

01:01:36.794 --> 01:01:41.165
YOU THE ONLY ONE OF US
WHO MADE IT OUT THAT NIGHT.

01:01:41.198 --> 01:01:43.734
THE ONLY ONE.

01:02:14.331 --> 01:02:16.834
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

01:02:21.005 --> 01:02:24.474
I DIDN'T PLAN
ON TELLING YOU ALL THAT.

01:02:28.178 --> 01:02:30.414
I'M SORRY.

01:02:32.783 --> 01:02:35.419
I DIDN'T PLAN
ON HEARIN' IT.

01:02:37.955 --> 01:02:41.658
DIDN'T PLAN ON YOU
WALKIN' DOWN THAT ROAD
NEITHER,

01:02:41.691 --> 01:02:44.128
COMIN' INTO MY HOUSE,

01:02:44.161 --> 01:02:46.797
BRINGIN' ALL THIS
WITH YOU.

01:02:53.037 --> 01:02:55.439
[ Denver Humming ]

01:02:59.343 --> 01:03:01.611
[ Denver Giggling ]

01:03:04.982 --> 01:03:09.186
WHERE'D YOU LEARN
TO DANCE ?
NOWHERE !

01:03:09.219 --> 01:03:11.788
WATCH ME DO THIS.

01:03:11.822 --> 01:03:13.590
OHH !

01:03:13.623 --> 01:03:16.160
[ Laughing ]
NOW YOU ! COME ON !

01:03:16.193 --> 01:03:19.329
YOU MAY AS WELL.
JUST GO ON !

01:03:19.363 --> 01:03:21.331
[ Laughing ]

01:03:21.365 --> 01:03:24.134
[ Screaming ]

01:03:27.571 --> 01:03:30.174
[ Groaning, Sighing ]

01:03:40.250 --> 01:03:43.553
WHY YOU CALL YOURSELF
BELOVED ?

01:03:44.922 --> 01:03:49.960
IN THE DARK,
MY NAME BELOVED.

01:03:49.994 --> 01:03:54.965
WHAT'S IT LIKE
WHERE YOU WAS BEFORE ?
CAN YOU TELL ME ?

01:03:54.999 --> 01:03:59.870
DARK. I WAS SMALL
IN THAT PLACE...

01:04:00.737 --> 01:04:03.407
LIKE THIS HERE.

01:04:03.440 --> 01:04:05.910
WERE YOU
COLD ?
HOT !

01:04:05.943 --> 01:04:09.880
NOTHING TO BREATHE
DOWN THERE.

01:04:09.914 --> 01:04:14.751
NO ROOM TO MOVE.

01:04:17.287 --> 01:04:19.556
YOU SEE ANYBODY ?

01:04:20.457 --> 01:04:22.659
IT'S A LOT OF PEOPLE...

01:04:22.692 --> 01:04:24.461
DOWN THERE.

01:04:25.930 --> 01:04:28.432
SOME IS DEAD.

01:04:28.465 --> 01:04:32.970
YOU SEE JESUS ?
BABY SUGGS ?

01:04:34.304 --> 01:04:36.840
I DON'T KNOW.

01:04:36.873 --> 01:04:39.509
I DON'T KNOW
THE NAMES.

01:04:39.543 --> 01:04:43.647
WELL, WHAT YOU
COME BACK HERE FOR ?

01:04:45.950 --> 01:04:49.619
TO SEE HER FACE.

01:04:49.653 --> 01:04:51.956
MAMA'S ?

01:04:51.989 --> 01:04:54.191
SETHE'S ?

01:04:54.224 --> 01:04:57.294
SETHE.

01:04:57.327 --> 01:05:00.064
I REMEMBER !

01:05:01.331 --> 01:05:03.367
I REMEMBER !

01:05:03.400 --> 01:05:05.802
I WAS IN THE WATER.

01:05:05.835 --> 01:05:09.606
I SEE HER DIAMONDS
DOWN THERE.

01:05:14.678 --> 01:05:18.215
THEN SHE LEFT ME BEHIND...

01:05:18.248 --> 01:05:20.517
BY MYSELF.

01:05:24.421 --> 01:05:26.991
DON'T.

01:05:27.024 --> 01:05:30.194
YOU WON'T EVER LEAVE US,
WILL YA ?

01:05:32.997 --> 01:05:36.666
NO. NEVER.

01:05:36.700 --> 01:05:40.037
THIS IS WHERE I AM !

01:05:43.107 --> 01:05:44.574
DON'T TELL.

01:05:44.608 --> 01:05:47.811
PLEASE DON'T LET MAMA
KNOW WHO YOU ARE.
YOU HEAR ME ?

01:05:47.844 --> 01:05:49.179
DON'T TELL ME WHAT TO DO !

01:05:49.213 --> 01:05:52.983
DON'T YOU NEVER, NEVER
TELL ME WHAT TO DO !

01:05:53.017 --> 01:05:55.319
- BUT I'M ON YOUR SIDE !
- SHE THE ONE !

01:05:55.352 --> 01:05:56.987
SHE THE ONE I NEED !

01:05:57.021 --> 01:06:02.559
YOU CAN GO !
SHE THE ONE I HAVE TO HAVE !

01:06:26.650 --> 01:06:29.919
[ Mumbles ]

01:06:38.195 --> 01:06:41.198
TELL ME HOW SETHE...

01:06:41.231 --> 01:06:44.334
MAKE YOU IN THE BOAT.

01:06:48.272 --> 01:06:51.108
TELL ME.

01:06:53.877 --> 01:06:57.114
SHE NEVER TOLD ME
ALL OF IT.

01:06:58.715 --> 01:07:01.118
TELL ME.

01:07:02.952 --> 01:07:05.522
DENVER.

01:07:05.555 --> 01:07:10.094
TELL ME.
[ Crying ]

01:07:12.962 --> 01:07:15.099
WELL--

01:07:16.700 --> 01:07:18.768
MAMA WAS RUNNIN' !

01:07:18.802 --> 01:07:22.239
[ Bird Squawking ]
[ Sethe Panting ]

01:07:29.613 --> 01:07:31.981
[ Screaming ]

01:07:36.653 --> 01:07:39.989
[ Moaning ]

01:07:44.894 --> 01:07:48.598
[ Moaning Continues ]

01:07:48.632 --> 01:07:50.400
WHO IN THERE ?

01:07:51.801 --> 01:07:53.903
WHO THAT
BACK THERE ?

01:07:57.141 --> 01:07:59.909
[ Panting ]

01:07:59.943 --> 01:08:03.313
[ Chuckling ]
MY, MY, MY.

01:08:03.347 --> 01:08:05.149
MY, MY, MY, MY !

01:08:05.182 --> 01:08:09.286
IT'S A NIGGER !
IF THAT DON'T BEAT ALL !

01:08:10.354 --> 01:08:11.655
GIRL,

01:08:11.688 --> 01:08:13.923
YOU ABOUT THE SCARIEST-LOOKIN'
SOMETHIN' I EVER SAW.

01:08:13.957 --> 01:08:15.892
WHAT YOU DOIN'
WAY BACK UP HERE ?

01:08:15.925 --> 01:08:18.694
I'M RUNNIN'.

01:08:19.962 --> 01:08:21.831
THESE THE FEET
YOU RUNNIN' ON ?

01:08:21.865 --> 01:08:24.067
[ Groans ]
JESUS, MY !

01:08:24.100 --> 01:08:27.337
MISS, AM I IN OHIO ?
[ Gasps ]

01:08:27.371 --> 01:08:31.140
[ Chuckling ]
OHIO ? NO, GIRL,
YOU IN KENTUCKY.

01:08:31.175 --> 01:08:33.676
YOU ABOUT A THOUSAND MILES
AWAY FROM OHIO.

01:08:33.710 --> 01:08:36.180
YOU HAVIN' A BABY ?

01:08:36.212 --> 01:08:38.148
OH, MY !

01:08:38.182 --> 01:08:41.651
I EXPECT THIS BABY THERE
IS GONNA DIE
IN THESE WILD ONIONS.

01:08:41.685 --> 01:08:44.188
I GOTTA EAT ME SOMETHIN'.

01:08:44.220 --> 01:08:48.024
W-W-WHERE-WHERE WAS YOU
ON YOUR WAY TO-TO, MISS ?

01:08:48.057 --> 01:08:51.528
BOSTON.
GET ME SOME VELVET.

01:08:51.560 --> 01:08:55.332
IT'S A STORE CALLED WILSON'S.
THEY JUST HAVE
THE "PURTIEST" VELVET.

01:08:55.365 --> 01:08:58.167
YOU EVER SEEN VELVET
OR TOUCHED IT ?

01:08:58.202 --> 01:09:01.537
I-IF-- IF I DID,
I DIDN'T KNOW IT.

01:09:01.571 --> 01:09:03.939
VELVET I SEEN WAS BROWN,

01:09:03.973 --> 01:09:06.475
BUT IN BOSTON,
THEY GOT ALL COLORS.

01:09:08.877 --> 01:09:11.180
WHAT THEY CALL YOU ?

01:09:11.215 --> 01:09:13.649
L-LU.

01:09:13.683 --> 01:09:15.652
[ Nervously Chuckling ]

01:09:15.685 --> 01:09:18.988
WELL, WHAT YOU GONNA DO, LU ?
YOU JUST GONNA LAY HERE
AND FOAL ?

01:09:19.022 --> 01:09:23.393
I-- I-I CAN'T GET UP.
I-I CAN'T MOVE.

01:09:23.426 --> 01:09:26.895
OH, SURE, YOU CAN, LU.
COME ON. YOU STAY HERE,
THE SNAKES MIGHT GET YA.

01:09:26.930 --> 01:09:28.497
I CAN'T.
COME ON, COME ON.

01:09:28.532 --> 01:09:33.069
COME ON, COME ON.
COME ON.
[ Groaning ]

01:09:34.770 --> 01:09:36.673
COME ON !

01:09:36.706 --> 01:09:39.243
I WAS FISHIN' OFF
THE BEAVER ONCE

01:09:39.276 --> 01:09:41.411
WHEN A NIGGER
FLOATED RIGHT BY ME.

01:09:41.444 --> 01:09:45.014
I DON'T LIKE
DROWNED PEOPLE MUCH.
DO YOU ?

01:09:46.916 --> 01:09:49.586
YOUR FEET KINDA
REMINDED ME OF HIM.

01:09:49.618 --> 01:09:51.787
ALL SWOLL-LIKE.

01:09:54.291 --> 01:09:56.426
NOW THIS IS GONNA
HURT A LITTLE.
[ Groaning ]

01:09:56.460 --> 01:09:58.695
ANYTHING DEAD
COMIN' BACK
TO LIFE HURTS.

01:09:58.728 --> 01:10:03.066
YOU AIN'T GOT NO BUSINESS
POKIN' 'ROUND THESE HILLS,
MISS.

01:10:03.099 --> 01:10:05.068
LOOKIT HERE
WHO'S TALKIN'.

01:10:05.101 --> 01:10:07.437
AIN'T NOBODY AFTER ME,
BUT I KNOW SOMEBODY
AFTER YOU,

01:10:07.471 --> 01:10:10.840
AND THEY CATCH YOU,
THEY'RE GONNA CUT
YOUR HEAD OFF.

01:10:10.874 --> 01:10:13.943
STOP WIGGLING, GIRL.
MY BACK HURT ME.

01:10:13.977 --> 01:10:15.612
YOUR BACK ?
YEAH.

01:10:15.645 --> 01:10:19.749
GIRL, YOU A MESS.
TURN OVER HERE
AND LET ME SEE.

01:10:19.783 --> 01:10:22.151
[ Groaning ]

01:10:33.963 --> 01:10:36.833
[ Screaming,
Moaning ]

01:10:37.734 --> 01:10:40.904
COME HERE.
JESUS !

01:10:42.906 --> 01:10:45.108
IT'S A TREE, LU.

01:10:45.141 --> 01:10:47.911
YOUR BACK GOT
A WHOLE TREE ON IT.

01:10:47.944 --> 01:10:51.147
CHOKECHERRY TREE
IN BLOOM.

01:10:51.180 --> 01:10:53.483
SEE ? HERE'S THE TRUNK.

01:10:53.517 --> 01:10:59.155
IT'S SPREAD
AND SPLIT WIDE OPEN,
FULL OF SAP AND BRANCHES.

01:10:59.188 --> 01:11:03.059
AND DARNED IF THESE
AIN'T BLOSSOMS.

01:11:03.092 --> 01:11:06.029
COME ON, GIRL.
[ Gasping ]

01:11:08.197 --> 01:11:11.000
'CAUSE OF ME,
YOU'RE UP AND WALKIN'.

01:11:11.034 --> 01:11:14.170
SEE, JESUS.
LU MADE IT THROUGH.

01:11:14.203 --> 01:11:16.673
I'M GOOD
WITH SICK THINGS,
AIN'T I ?

01:11:16.706 --> 01:11:19.776
YEAH, YOU GOOD.

01:11:19.809 --> 01:11:23.347
WHAT'S ALL OVER
YOUR DRESS, GIRL ?
IT'S MILK.

01:11:23.380 --> 01:11:25.415
GOTTA GET MILK
TO MY BABY GIRL.

01:11:25.449 --> 01:11:28.685
YOU MEAN, YOU GOT
ANOTHER BABY WAITIN'
FOR YOU ?

01:11:28.718 --> 01:11:30.887
OH, MY, JESUS.

01:11:34.057 --> 01:11:38.194
[ Panting ]
COME ON.

01:11:47.036 --> 01:11:51.307
COME ON.
COME ON.

01:11:52.909 --> 01:11:55.545
[ Giggling ]
NOW...

01:11:56.713 --> 01:11:58.982
THAT'S OHIO.

01:12:25.442 --> 01:12:27.110
[ Giggling ]

01:12:35.251 --> 01:12:37.854
JESUS LOOKIN'
AT YOU, GIRL !

01:12:37.887 --> 01:12:39.589
[ Laughing ]

01:12:40.724 --> 01:12:42.926
WHOO !
COME ON.

01:12:42.959 --> 01:12:46.329
[ Groaning ]

01:12:46.362 --> 01:12:49.533
OH, HERE'S YOUR PADDLE !

01:12:54.604 --> 01:12:58.174
[ Screaming ]
WHAT YOU DOIN' NOW,
POOR GIRL ?

01:12:58.207 --> 01:13:01.578
[ Gasping ]
STOP THAT RIGHT NOW !

01:13:01.611 --> 01:13:05.749
JESUS, LU !
STOP IT ! STOP IT !
[ Panting ]

01:13:05.782 --> 01:13:08.284
LU ! LU !
STOP IT !

01:13:08.317 --> 01:13:11.621
OH, JESUS !
I'M AWFULLY SORRY
ABOUT BRAGGIN'.

01:13:11.655 --> 01:13:13.923
I NEED YOU HERE NOW !

01:13:13.957 --> 01:13:18.094
DON'T BE GETTIN' LOST
ON ME NOW, JESUS !
[ Continues Panting ]

01:13:18.127 --> 01:13:21.297
COME ON !
PUSH ! PUSH !

01:13:21.330 --> 01:13:23.900
[ Screaming ]
PUSH !

01:13:23.933 --> 01:13:25.469
OH, HERE COMES THE HEAD.

01:13:25.502 --> 01:13:28.705
OH, DEAR JESUS,
PLEASE, HELP !

01:13:28.738 --> 01:13:30.574
GOD, IT'S STUCK !

01:13:30.607 --> 01:13:34.644
[ Grunting ]
COME ON !
[ Screaming ]

01:13:34.678 --> 01:13:37.814
[ Panting ]

01:13:37.847 --> 01:13:40.283
[ Laughing ]
[ Baby Crying ]

01:13:47.290 --> 01:13:51.094
OH, PRAISE JESUS.
PRAISE JESUS.

01:13:51.127 --> 01:13:53.262
[ Crying Continues ]

01:14:05.709 --> 01:14:08.612
SHE AIN'T NEVER
GONNA KNOW WHO I AM.

01:14:11.881 --> 01:14:14.918
YOU BETTER TELL HER
WHO BRUNG HER
INTO THIS WORLD.

01:14:14.951 --> 01:14:16.786
[ Crying ]

01:14:16.820 --> 01:14:20.790
YOU SAY,
"MISS AMY DENVER...

01:14:20.824 --> 01:14:23.392
OF BOSTON."
MM.

01:14:24.360 --> 01:14:28.164
PRETTY.
THAT'S PRETTY.

01:14:29.165 --> 01:14:30.800
DENVER.

01:14:32.135 --> 01:14:38.141
REAL PRETTY.
SHH.

01:14:38.174 --> 01:14:41.711
[ Denver Narrating ]
SO AMY DENVER, SHE LEFT
ME AND MAMA ON THE RIVERBANK.

01:14:41.745 --> 01:14:45.248
THAT WAS THE FIRST TIME
WE MET STAMP PAID.

01:14:47.150 --> 01:14:49.553
[ Denver Crying ]

01:15:12.108 --> 01:15:15.211
HEY THERE.

01:15:15.244 --> 01:15:17.380
YOU HEADIN' ACROSS ?

01:15:19.048 --> 01:15:21.417
YES, SIR.

01:15:21.450 --> 01:15:25.822
ANYBODY KNOW
YOU COMIN' ?

01:15:25.855 --> 01:15:29.458
YES, SIR.
MY MOTHER-IN-LAW,
BABY SUGGS.

01:15:30.794 --> 01:15:32.629
[ Crying Continues ]

01:15:59.789 --> 01:16:02.859
[ Denver Narrating ]
MOST FOLK CALL HER
BABY SUGGS HOLY.

01:16:02.892 --> 01:16:06.896
TO ME,
SHE WERE GRANDMA BABY.
[ Laughing ]

01:16:09.599 --> 01:16:13.402
THANK YOU, ELLA.
THANK YOU, STAMP.

01:16:14.838 --> 01:16:17.140
[ Laughing ]
OH !

01:16:17.173 --> 01:16:21.144
[ Laughing Continues ]

01:16:21.177 --> 01:16:25.081
OH, MY LORD.

01:16:25.114 --> 01:16:27.984
MY SWEET JESUS !

01:16:28.017 --> 01:16:30.586
THANK YOU !

01:16:30.620 --> 01:16:34.323
[ Baby Suggs Laughing ]
[ Sethe Crying ]

01:16:34.357 --> 01:16:36.392
WHERE'S MY HALLE ?

01:16:36.425 --> 01:16:38.762
WELL,
HE W-WASN'T THERE...

01:16:38.795 --> 01:16:42.498
WHERE HE SAID TO MEET HIM,
AND I HAD TO GO.

01:16:42.531 --> 01:16:44.400
HAD TO.

01:16:44.433 --> 01:16:46.335
H-H-HE'LL MAKE IT.

01:16:46.369 --> 01:16:50.606
IF I MADE IT,
HALLE SURE CAN.

01:16:50.640 --> 01:16:54.443
WHERE-WHERE'S
MY CHILDREN ?
OH, NO, NOT NOW.

01:16:54.477 --> 01:16:56.412
WE GOT TO
FIX YOU UP FIRST.

01:16:56.445 --> 01:17:00.549
YOU TOO UGLY-LOOKIN'
TO WAKE 'EM.
[ Laughing ]

01:17:05.021 --> 01:17:08.658
SHH.
[ Door Opening ]

01:17:10.559 --> 01:17:14.297
BUGLAR, HOWARD !
[ Both ]
MAMA, MAMA !

01:17:15.364 --> 01:17:18.835
OH, LOOK AT YOU.
[ Children Laughing ]

01:17:18.868 --> 01:17:20.970
LET ME SEE.
OH !

01:17:21.004 --> 01:17:23.372
TELL ME THE OTHER BABY.

01:17:23.406 --> 01:17:25.675
TELL ME YOU BIG SISTER.

01:17:25.709 --> 01:17:28.878
[ Denver ]
MM, BABY SUGGS CALL HER...

01:17:28.912 --> 01:17:32.882
CRAWLIN' ALREADY BABY.

01:17:32.916 --> 01:17:36.786
CRAWLIN' ALREADY ?
AIN'T THIS SOMETHIN' ?

01:17:36.820 --> 01:17:40.489
ALL RIGHT, BABY GIRL.
RIGHT THIS WAY.

01:17:40.523 --> 01:17:42.726
MAMA'S WAITIN'.

01:17:47.330 --> 01:17:50.033
ALL RIGHT,
HOWARD, BUGLAR.

01:17:50.066 --> 01:17:52.035
[ Crying ]

01:17:55.104 --> 01:17:57.974
YOU'RE OKAY.
YEAH.

01:17:58.007 --> 01:18:01.410
AIN'T NOTHIN' HERE
WORTH SAVIN'.

01:18:01.444 --> 01:18:04.881
WHAT IS THIS ?

01:18:04.914 --> 01:18:07.683
WEDDIN' PRESENT
FROM MRS. GARNER.

01:18:09.185 --> 01:18:13.456
I WISH THERE WAS A GROOM
TO GO WITH IT.

01:18:22.398 --> 01:18:24.467
PUT 'EM ON, CHILD.

01:18:25.534 --> 01:18:29.538
MAYBE THEY'LL
LIGHT HIS WAY.

01:18:32.876 --> 01:18:35.411
LOOK AT THOSE SHINE.

01:18:35.444 --> 01:18:37.781
PRETTY, HUH ?

01:18:41.284 --> 01:18:44.320
DADDY COME SOON, HUH ?

01:18:46.389 --> 01:18:49.358
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPEN,

01:18:49.392 --> 01:18:52.661
GOD HAS LED YOU HOME.

01:18:53.963 --> 01:18:55.631
SO...

01:18:55.664 --> 01:18:58.234
LAY 'EM DOWN, SETHE.

01:18:58.267 --> 01:19:01.304
SWORD AND SHIELD.

01:19:01.337 --> 01:19:04.040
STUDY WAR NO MORE.

01:19:04.073 --> 01:19:06.910
GOD HAS LED YOU HOME.

01:19:11.414 --> 01:19:16.019
WHERE WE GOIN', MAMA ?
WE GOIN' TO PAY TRIBUTE
TO YOUR DADDY.

01:19:17.787 --> 01:19:20.623
OUR HOUSE USED TO BE
A WHOLE DIFFERENT THING.

01:19:20.656 --> 01:19:22.558
STRANGERS RESTED THERE.

01:19:22.591 --> 01:19:26.495
PEOPLE LEAVIN' MESSAGES.
FOLKS COMIN' AND GOIN'
ALL THE TIME.

01:19:26.529 --> 01:19:30.800
IT WAS A HAPPY HOUSE WHEN
I FIRST GOT THERE WITH DENVER
STRAPPED TO MY CHEST...

01:19:30.834 --> 01:19:33.336
WAITIN' ON HER DADDY
TO COME.

01:19:33.369 --> 01:19:35.004
DADDY.

01:19:35.038 --> 01:19:38.607
HALLE BOUGHT
BABY SUGGS' FREEDOM,

01:19:38.641 --> 01:19:41.010
BUT SLAVERY DONE ALREADY
BUSTED HER LEGS...

01:19:41.044 --> 01:19:44.814
AND BUSTED HER BACK,
HANDS, EVERYTHING.

01:19:44.848 --> 01:19:48.351
WHEN SHE COME HERE,
SHE AIN'T HAD NOTHIN' LEFT
TO MAKE NO LIVIN' WITH...

01:19:48.384 --> 01:19:51.821
BESIDES HER HEART.

01:19:56.059 --> 01:19:59.128
BABY SUGGS USED TO PREACH
RIGHT HERE.

01:20:01.364 --> 01:20:04.200
LET THE CHILDREN COME.

01:20:04.233 --> 01:20:07.136
[ Laughing ]
[ Footsteps ]

01:20:08.838 --> 01:20:13.009
LET YOUR MOTHERS
HEAR YOU LAUGH.

01:20:13.042 --> 01:20:15.644
[ Children Laughing ]

01:20:28.157 --> 01:20:30.894
LET THE GROWN MEN COME.

01:20:38.935 --> 01:20:43.406
LET YOUR WIVES
AND YOUR CHILDREN...

01:20:43.439 --> 01:20:46.175
SEE YOU DANCE.

01:20:48.777 --> 01:20:51.614
[ Crowd Cheering,
Chattering ]

01:21:17.106 --> 01:21:21.677
WOMEN !
WOMEN !

01:21:21.710 --> 01:21:23.980
I WANT YOU TO WEEP !

01:21:25.548 --> 01:21:27.716
JUST WEEP...

01:21:30.553 --> 01:21:32.989
FOR THE LIVING,

01:21:34.157 --> 01:21:36.259
FOR THE DEAD.

01:21:38.461 --> 01:21:41.264
WEEP.

01:22:06.922 --> 01:22:11.660
GRANDMA BABY USED TO SAY
YOUR DADDY WAS TOO GOOD
FOR THIS WORLD.

01:22:11.694 --> 01:22:13.196
REMEMBER ?

01:22:14.697 --> 01:22:17.066
HE WAS A GOOD MAN.

01:22:17.100 --> 01:22:18.801
IT SCARED HER.

01:22:18.834 --> 01:22:20.503
SHE USED TO ALWAYS FRET

01:22:20.536 --> 01:22:23.839
WHETHER HE WASN'T GONNA
MAKE IT THROUGH NOTHIN'.

01:22:23.872 --> 01:22:27.276
HE MADE IT THROUGH A LOT.

01:22:27.310 --> 01:22:30.046
MAYBE GRANDMA BABY
WAS RIGHT.

01:22:35.551 --> 01:22:37.220
DENVER...

01:22:38.687 --> 01:22:41.890
YOUR DADDY AIN'T GONNA
NEVER SHOW UP HERE.

01:22:43.459 --> 01:22:46.662
YOU UNDERSTAND ?
BUT--

01:22:49.065 --> 01:22:51.867
THE DAY AIN'T GONNA
NEVER COME...

01:22:51.900 --> 01:22:56.339
WHEN HALLE KNOCKS
ON THAT DOOR.

01:22:56.372 --> 01:22:57.906
NEVER.

01:23:10.986 --> 01:23:12.355
THERE--

01:23:21.364 --> 01:23:23.366
MAMA !

01:23:40.549 --> 01:23:42.751
PAUL !

01:23:42.785 --> 01:23:45.754
PAUL D !
PAUL D !

01:23:45.788 --> 01:23:47.423
YOU HERE ?

01:23:47.456 --> 01:23:52.661
[ Laughing ]
WHERE ELSE WOULD I BE
ON A SUNDAY OFF ?

01:23:52.695 --> 01:23:55.098
[ Water Splashing ]

01:24:02.905 --> 01:24:06.242
[ Panting ]
YOU'RE HERE.

01:24:07.310 --> 01:24:10.113
UH-HUH.

01:24:10.146 --> 01:24:13.216
WHY DON'T YOU
COME ON IN HERE ?
[ Laughing ]

01:24:16.051 --> 01:24:18.421
GIRLS RIGHT
BEHIND ME.

01:24:18.454 --> 01:24:20.889
I DON'T HEAR
NOBODY.

01:24:21.990 --> 01:24:25.128
TTA COOK.
ME TOO.

01:24:34.137 --> 01:24:36.305
YEAH, YEAH.

01:24:43.912 --> 01:24:47.150
I THOUGHT I'D MAKE
SOME SNAP BEANS.

01:24:57.193 --> 01:25:00.363
FRY UP
A LITTLE CORN.
YEAH.

01:25:04.367 --> 01:25:06.802
PAUL D, STOP IT.
STOP IT.

01:25:06.835 --> 01:25:10.406
[ Paul D Whispering ]
DENVER ?

01:25:10.439 --> 01:25:14.677
BELOVED ? THAT YOU ?
[ Paul D ]
SHH, SHH.

01:25:14.710 --> 01:25:18.080
[ Sethe Slapping
Paul D ]
PAUL D !

01:25:18.113 --> 01:25:20.349
[ Paul D Chuckling ]
COME ON.

01:25:20.383 --> 01:25:22.885
[ Sethe Giggling ]

01:25:24.853 --> 01:25:28.224
[ Whimpering ]

01:25:31.827 --> 01:25:34.163
[ Crying ]

01:25:43.806 --> 01:25:46.209
[ Crying Continues ]

01:27:08.791 --> 01:27:10.926
[ Calling ]

01:27:26.008 --> 01:27:28.444
[ Beloved Wheezing ]

01:27:28.477 --> 01:27:31.880
THAT WAS REAL FINE, SETHE.
THANK YOU.

01:27:31.914 --> 01:27:34.082
SURE YOU GOT
ENOUGH ?
YES, MA'AM.

01:27:34.116 --> 01:27:36.919
BONE-TIRED
AND RIVER-WHIPPED.

01:27:36.952 --> 01:27:39.355
[ Dishes Clattering ]

01:27:42.024 --> 01:27:44.360
[ Sethe Chattering ]

01:28:22.197 --> 01:28:25.300
PAUL D.
[ Groaning ]

01:28:27.903 --> 01:28:31.707
DON'T TELL ME
I SLEPT IN THIS CHAIR
THE WHOLE NIGHT.

01:28:31.740 --> 01:28:34.209
I'M NOT GONNA SAY
A THING.

01:28:34.242 --> 01:28:36.278
WHY YOU DIDN'T
ROUSE ME ?
I DID.

01:28:36.311 --> 01:28:38.481
I TRIED CALLIN' YOU
TWO OR THREE TIMES.

01:28:38.514 --> 01:28:41.550
I THOUGHT MAYBE
YOU WENT OUT SOMEWHERE.
SORRY, HONEY.

01:28:41.584 --> 01:28:45.187
I'LL MAKE US
SOME BREAKFAST.
YOU KNOW SOMETHIN' ?

01:28:45.220 --> 01:28:48.090
BREAKFAST CAN WAIT.
[ Chuckling ]

01:28:50.158 --> 01:28:55.030
PAUL ! PAUL D !
PAUL D !
[ Paul D Snoring ]

01:28:55.063 --> 01:28:58.401
WHAT YOU DOIN'
IN BABY SUGGS' BED ?

01:28:58.434 --> 01:29:00.569
I DON'T KNOW.

01:29:01.704 --> 01:29:05.408
LIKE I'M HAVIN'
HOUSE FITS.

01:29:05.441 --> 01:29:08.744
IT GOT ME
TO MOVE FROM BED...

01:29:08.777 --> 01:29:11.046
TO CHAIR TO BED.

01:29:12.114 --> 01:29:14.282
SLEPT GOOD, THOUGH.

01:29:15.551 --> 01:29:18.587
NO. COME ON NOW.
YOU GONNA BE LATE
FOR WORK.

01:29:18.621 --> 01:29:22.124
COME ON, COME ON.
I GOT TO GET TO WORK.
SO DO YOU.

01:29:24.460 --> 01:29:26.429
COME ON.

01:29:26.462 --> 01:29:29.231
YEAH, RIGHT.

01:29:29.264 --> 01:29:32.000
COME ON,
BELOVED.
YEAH.

01:29:32.034 --> 01:29:34.437
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

01:29:52.721 --> 01:29:56.191
[ Beloved ]
WHY DON'T THE CHICKENS
HAVE NO TEETH ?

01:29:56.224 --> 01:29:58.627
[ Sethe Laughing ]

01:29:58.661 --> 01:30:01.930
[ Beloved Mumbling ]
[ Sethe ]
WHOO !

01:30:01.964 --> 01:30:06.134
CHICKEN HAS NO TEETH.
[ Sethe Laughing ]

01:30:06.168 --> 01:30:10.172
MAMA'S COOKIN' CHICKEN !

01:30:29.925 --> 01:30:33.161
[ Paul D Moaning ]

01:30:40.703 --> 01:30:45.173
OH, GOD.
[ Gasps ]

01:30:47.042 --> 01:30:49.177
HEAD HURTS.

01:31:44.833 --> 01:31:47.670
WHAT YOU WANT
IN HERE ?

01:31:54.877 --> 01:32:00.148
I WANT YOU TOUCH ME...

01:32:00.182 --> 01:32:03.351
ON THE INSIDE PART...

01:32:03.385 --> 01:32:05.754
AND CALL MY NAME.

01:32:05.788 --> 01:32:11.594
GOOD PEOPLE TAKE YOU IN,
TREAT YOU GOOD,

01:32:11.627 --> 01:32:15.097
YOU OUGHTA TRY
TO BE GOOD BACK.

01:32:15.130 --> 01:32:17.232
YOU DON'T--

01:32:17.265 --> 01:32:19.568
SETHE LOVES YOU...

01:32:19.602 --> 01:32:21.770
AS MUCH AS
HER OWN DAUGHTER,
YOU KNOW THAT.

01:32:21.804 --> 01:32:24.940
SHE DON'T LOVE ME
LIKE I LOVE HER.

01:32:24.973 --> 01:32:27.910
I DON'T LOVE NOBODY
BUT HER.

01:32:27.943 --> 01:32:30.646
THEN WHAT YOU COME
IN HERE FOR ?

01:32:34.149 --> 01:32:39.087
I WANT YOU TO TOUCH ME
ON THE INSIDE PART.

01:32:39.121 --> 01:32:43.158
GO BACK IN THAT HOUSE
AND GET IN THAT BED.

01:32:48.563 --> 01:32:53.301
YOU HAS TO TOUCH ME
ON THE INSIDE PART.

01:32:53.335 --> 01:32:56.939
YOU HAS TO CALL ME
MY NAME.

01:32:56.972 --> 01:32:58.641
NO !

01:32:58.674 --> 01:33:01.309
NO.
I'LL GO
IF YOU CALL IT.

01:33:01.343 --> 01:33:05.681
NO, BELOVED.
PLEASE, CALL IT.

01:33:07.082 --> 01:33:09.051
BELOVED.

01:33:09.084 --> 01:33:11.286
[ Groaning ]

01:33:12.287 --> 01:33:14.657
BELOVED.

01:33:19.094 --> 01:33:20.629
RED HEART.

01:33:22.097 --> 01:33:25.000
RED HEART.

01:33:25.033 --> 01:33:27.936
RED HEART.

01:33:27.970 --> 01:33:30.172
RED HEART.

01:33:30.205 --> 01:33:33.608
RED HEART.
RED HEART.

01:33:37.212 --> 01:33:39.915
[ Paul D ]
RED HEART.

01:33:39.948 --> 01:33:43.151
RED HEART.
RED HEART !

01:33:43.185 --> 01:33:44.920
RED HEART !

01:33:44.953 --> 01:33:47.690
RED HEART.
RED HEART.

01:33:49.291 --> 01:33:52.194
[ Paul D Crying ]

01:33:52.227 --> 01:33:54.396
[ Screaming ]

01:33:58.801 --> 01:34:02.237
[ Crying Continues ]

01:34:07.743 --> 01:34:11.046
ARE THERE FLOWERS
IN THE DARK ?

01:34:11.079 --> 01:34:13.248
THERE IS.

01:34:25.560 --> 01:34:32.000
[ Steamship Whistling ]
[ Man Yelling ]

01:34:34.036 --> 01:34:36.404
[ Yelling Continues ]

01:34:41.276 --> 01:34:44.079
[ Men Chattering ]

01:34:44.112 --> 01:34:46.849
COME ON.
COME ON.
WHOO-HOO !

01:34:46.882 --> 01:34:50.685
[ Paul D Mumbling ]

01:34:50.719 --> 01:34:53.922
PAUL D !
WANNA RIDE WITH US ?

01:34:53.956 --> 01:34:57.926
WE GOT THE WAGON TODAY.
WHY DON'T WE--

01:35:16.812 --> 01:35:20.448
[ Whispering ]
IF I COULD
JUST TELL HER.

01:35:39.601 --> 01:35:44.506
[ Paul D ]
NOW, SETHE, YOU AIN'T GONNA LIKE
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO SAY.

01:35:45.841 --> 01:35:48.376
SOMETHIN' IS HAPPENING
TO ME.

01:35:48.410 --> 01:35:50.813
THAT GIRL DO IT.

01:35:52.848 --> 01:35:57.886
FIXIN' ME. YEAH.
SHE FIXED ME, SETHE.

01:35:57.920 --> 01:36:01.790
SHE FIXED ME,
AND I CAN'T BREAK IT.

01:36:01.824 --> 01:36:04.159
SHE-SHE MOVED ME
OUT OF THE HOUSE,

01:36:04.192 --> 01:36:07.996
AND THEN SHE--
SHE JOINED ME.

01:36:08.030 --> 01:36:09.998
NO.

01:36:11.133 --> 01:36:14.102
PAUL D ?
[ Dog Barking ]

01:36:14.136 --> 01:36:16.104
PAUL D ?

01:36:17.472 --> 01:36:19.908
WHY, YOU MAKE ME FEEL
LIKE A YOUNG GIRL,

01:36:19.942 --> 01:36:23.778
COMIN' BY TO PICK ME UP
AFTER WORK.

01:36:23.812 --> 01:36:27.249
PUPSKI.
THERE YOU GO, PUPSKI.

01:36:27.282 --> 01:36:32.620
BETTER WATCH OUT.
I MIGHT START
LOOKIN' FORWARD TO IT.

01:36:32.654 --> 01:36:35.023
YOU GET OFF FROM WORK
EARLY OR WHAT ?

01:36:36.458 --> 01:36:38.793
I TOOK OFF EARLY.

01:36:38.827 --> 01:36:43.498
[ Horse Whinnying ]
ANYTHING THE MATTER ?

01:36:43.531 --> 01:36:46.568
IN A WAY OF SPEAKIN'.

01:36:51.206 --> 01:36:56.011
SETHE, YOU AIN'T GONNA LIKE
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO SAY.

01:36:57.812 --> 01:37:02.017
WELL, SAY IT, PAUL D,
WHETHER I LIKE IT OR NOT.

01:37:05.921 --> 01:37:08.991
I WANT YOU PREGNANT.

01:37:19.034 --> 01:37:20.735
YOU WANT ME PREGNANT ?

01:37:22.004 --> 01:37:25.573
IS THAT WHAT
YOU COME BY HERE FOR ?

01:37:25.607 --> 01:37:29.244
DON'T YOU THINK
I'M A LITTLE TOO OLD
TO START THAT ALL OVER AGAIN ?

01:37:29.277 --> 01:37:31.313
TH-THINK ABOUT IT.

01:37:31.346 --> 01:37:33.181
[ Paul D Laughing ]

01:37:40.555 --> 01:37:42.624
YOU CRAZY MAN.

01:37:46.294 --> 01:37:48.096
COME ON.

01:37:48.130 --> 01:37:51.033
[ Laughing Continues ]

01:38:01.876 --> 01:38:04.046
[ Sethe ]
WHAT HAS GOT INTO YOU ?

01:38:04.079 --> 01:38:08.116
YOU NEED SOME BABIES
OR SOMEBODY TO PLAY WITH.

01:38:08.150 --> 01:38:12.554
I'M SURE WILLIN' TO TRY.
I NEED A WILLIN' PARTNER
THOUGH.

01:38:12.587 --> 01:38:15.057
I'LL SAY.
I'LL SAY.

01:38:23.831 --> 01:38:25.968
MERCY.

01:38:27.235 --> 01:38:29.804
LET'S RUN.
LET'S RUN.

01:38:29.837 --> 01:38:32.640
I'VE BEEN ON MY FEET
ALL DAY.

01:38:32.674 --> 01:38:35.043
OH, WHERE I BEEN,
SETHE ?

01:38:35.077 --> 01:38:38.880
STOP, PAUL D.
MY LEGS AIN'T MADE
FOR THIS.

01:38:38.913 --> 01:38:40.782
[ Laughing ]

01:38:40.815 --> 01:38:43.818
* HARD WORK AIN'T EASY

01:38:43.851 --> 01:38:48.223
* DRY BREAD AIN'T GREASY
[ Laughing ]

01:38:48.256 --> 01:38:51.826
* LITTLE RICE
LITTLE BEAN *

01:38:51.859 --> 01:38:53.728
HEY, STAMP !
STAMP PAID !

01:38:53.761 --> 01:38:56.164
I'M GONNA TAKE
THIS ONE HOME
WITH ME !

01:38:56.198 --> 01:39:00.468
[ Yelling, Laughing ]

01:39:00.502 --> 01:39:04.172
HEY, YOU LIKE THIS WORK SO MUCH,
MAYBE YOU BEST GET IN THE CHUTE
WITH THE OTHERS.

01:39:04.206 --> 01:39:06.741
YOU AIN'T GOT MUCH MORE SENSE
THAN THEY DO.

01:39:06.774 --> 01:39:09.077
* NO MEAT IN BETWEEN

01:39:09.111 --> 01:39:11.013
I AIN'T SINGIN'
ABOUT THIS !

01:39:11.046 --> 01:39:14.316
IF A MAN CAN MAKE A PLAN,
THE MAN CAN MAKE
THE GOOD TIMES HAPPEN.

01:39:14.349 --> 01:39:18.620
THE MAN GOT PLANS ?
YOU SAVIN' UP
FOR A GOLD MINE, BOY ?

01:39:18.653 --> 01:39:22.690
BETTER THAN GOLD.
ME AND MY WOMAN'S PLANNIN'
ON STARTIN' A FAMILY.

01:39:22.724 --> 01:39:26.028
YEAH, A NEW LIFE.
BORN FREE !

01:39:26.061 --> 01:39:28.796
NOW, IF THAT DON'T MEAN
A GOOD TIME,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT DOES.

01:39:28.830 --> 01:39:31.599
NOTHIN' BORN FREE
EVER AGAIN.

01:39:31.633 --> 01:39:34.869
WHAT YOU TALKIN' ?

01:39:34.902 --> 01:39:37.372
I BEEN BOUGHT AND SOLD
FIVE TIMES.

01:39:37.405 --> 01:39:41.043
THE LAST TIME,
TO THE NORTHPOINT BANK
AND RAILWAY COMPANY.

01:39:41.076 --> 01:39:45.980
NO MORE !
I WALK AND I SLEEP
AND I EAT WHERE I PLEASE.

01:39:46.014 --> 01:39:48.150
I EARN A FREE MAN'S WAGE.

01:39:48.183 --> 01:39:50.885
NOBODY'S GONNA OWN US
NO MORE.

01:39:50.918 --> 01:39:53.288
NOBODY'S GONNA OWN
MY CHILDREN EITHER.

01:39:53.321 --> 01:39:55.957
NO MORE !
NO MORE !

01:39:55.990 --> 01:39:58.726
CHILDREN INHERIT
WHERE THEY COME FROM.

01:39:58.760 --> 01:40:03.198
JUST 'CAUSE YOU CAN'T SEE
NO CHAINS DON'T MEAN
THEY NOT THERE.

01:40:03.231 --> 01:40:08.970
AND AS LONG
AS THE WORLD IS WHITE,
THAT'S WHERE WE STAYIN'.

01:40:09.003 --> 01:40:11.173
COME ON.
LET'S GO GET SOMETHIN' TO EAT.

01:40:11.206 --> 01:40:14.676
COME ON.
COME ON.

01:40:17.112 --> 01:40:20.082
[ Hogs Squealing ]

01:40:21.783 --> 01:40:24.886
MIND IF I JOIN YOU ?

01:40:24.919 --> 01:40:28.356
FREE COUNTRY,
NO MATTER WHAT NOBODY SAY.

01:40:35.930 --> 01:40:39.033
YOU DON'T KNOW,
DO YOU, SON ?

01:40:39.067 --> 01:40:42.404
KNOW WHAT ?

01:40:42.437 --> 01:40:46.108
YOU ONE OF BABY SUGGS'
SWEET HOME MEN, AIN'T YA ?

01:40:46.141 --> 01:40:47.909
YES, SIR.

01:40:47.942 --> 01:40:52.714
ME. MY BROTHERS.
HER SON, HALLE.

01:40:52.747 --> 01:40:54.949
YOU KNEW BABY ?
OH, YEAH.

01:40:54.982 --> 01:40:58.753
BABY SUGGS HOLY.
GOD REST HER SOUL.

01:40:58.786 --> 01:41:02.857
YEAH. SETHE TOLD ME
SHE DIED SOFT AS CREAM.

01:41:02.890 --> 01:41:06.228
WELL, MAYBE
ON THE OUTSIDE.

01:41:06.261 --> 01:41:09.164
WHY IS THAT ?

01:41:14.402 --> 01:41:17.305
[ Papers Shuffling ]

01:41:23.745 --> 01:41:30.084
IT WAS ME WHO HAD BRUNG SETHE
ACROSS THE RIVER WHEN
SHE RUN AWAY FROM SWEET HOME.

01:41:32.154 --> 01:41:36.191
I WAS THERE
THE DAY IT HAPPENED.

01:41:41.196 --> 01:41:43.631
WHO IS IT ?

01:41:43.665 --> 01:41:47.001
THAT THERE'S
A PICTURE OF SETHE.

01:41:47.034 --> 01:41:49.204
SETHE ?

01:41:50.938 --> 01:41:53.841
[ Scoffs ]
THAT AIN'T HER MOUTH.

01:41:53.875 --> 01:41:57.245
I CAN SEE
WHY YOU MAY THINK IT,

01:41:57.279 --> 01:42:00.215
AROUND THE EYES.

01:42:02.217 --> 01:42:06.388
B-BUT THAT THERE
AIN'T HER MOUTH.

01:42:08.523 --> 01:42:13.995
BESIDES, WHY WOULD THEY PUT
SOME COLORED WOMAN'S PICTURE
IN THE PAPER ?

01:42:14.028 --> 01:42:17.332
YOU DON'T READ,
DO YOU, SON ?

01:42:23.004 --> 01:42:26.040
YOU WANT ME TO READ
TO YOU ?

01:42:28.576 --> 01:42:30.745
[ Sweeping ]

01:42:33.381 --> 01:42:35.517
[ Chattering, Distant ]

01:43:07.382 --> 01:43:09.551
[ Horse Whinnying ]

01:43:09.584 --> 01:43:14.121
ALREADY FED THE GIRLS.
YOU EAT ?

01:43:15.557 --> 01:43:17.124
WANT SOMETHING ?

01:43:43.150 --> 01:43:45.553
BEST YOU COME INSIDE.

01:44:05.273 --> 01:44:08.876
I DON'T HAVE TO TELL YOU
ABOUT SWEET HOME,

01:44:08.910 --> 01:44:11.879
WHAT IT WAS.

01:44:11.913 --> 01:44:18.620
MAYBE YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT WAS LIKE FOR ME
TO GET AWAY FROM THERE.

01:44:18.653 --> 01:44:21.756
I DID IT.
I GOT US ALL OUT.

01:44:21.789 --> 01:44:26.894
UP UNTIL THEN,
IT WAS THE ONLY THING
I EVER DID ON MY OWN.

01:44:26.928 --> 01:44:30.932
ME... USIN' MY OWN HEAD.

01:44:33.200 --> 01:44:36.538
BUT IT WAS MORE
THAN THAT.

01:44:37.839 --> 01:44:40.808
I WAS-- I WAS BIG...

01:44:40.842 --> 01:44:42.944
AND WIDE, PAUL.

01:44:42.977 --> 01:44:48.516
SO WIDE, WHEN I STRETCHED
OUT MY ARMS, ALL MY CHILDREN
COULD GET IN BETWEEN.

01:44:48.550 --> 01:44:52.820
LOOKED LIKE I--
LOOKED LIKE I LOVED 'EM MORE
AFTER WE GOT HERE.

01:44:52.854 --> 01:44:54.489
[ Chuckles ]

01:44:54.522 --> 01:44:55.657
MAYBE I JUST KNEW

01:44:55.690 --> 01:44:59.193
THAT LONG AS WE WAS IN
KENTUCKY WITH SCHOOLTEACHER,

01:44:59.226 --> 01:45:02.196
THEY REALLY WASN'T MINE
TO LOVE.

01:45:02.229 --> 01:45:04.932
LOOK LIKE WHEN
I JUMPED OFF THAT WAGON,

01:45:04.966 --> 01:45:10.405
WASN'T NOBODY IN THIS WORLD
I COULDN'T LOVE
IF I WANT TO.

01:45:11.839 --> 01:45:14.108
TWENTY-EIGHT DAYS.

01:45:14.141 --> 01:45:19.213
TWENTY-EIGHT GOOD DAYS
OF FREE LIFE.

01:45:19.246 --> 01:45:22.149
I'D WAKE UP
IN THE MORNING AND...

01:45:22.183 --> 01:45:26.921
DECIDE FOR MYSELF
WHAT TO DO WITH THE DAY.

01:45:28.089 --> 01:45:30.892
SOMETIMES I--
I HEAR MY BOYS--

01:45:30.925 --> 01:45:34.829
HEAR 'EM LAUGHIN' A LAUGH
I AIN'T NEVER HEARD.

01:45:34.862 --> 01:45:39.033
FIRST I GET SCARED, SCARED
SOMEBODY MIGHT HEAR 'EM...

01:45:39.066 --> 01:45:40.835
AND GET MAD.

01:45:40.868 --> 01:45:45.172
THEN I REMEMBERED
THAT IF THEY LAUGHED
THAT HARD TILL IT HURT,

01:45:45.206 --> 01:45:49.076
THAT'D BE THE ONLY HURT
THEY HAVE ALL DAY.

01:45:50.277 --> 01:45:52.847
AND WHEN THE PEOPLE
WOULD GATHER--

01:45:52.880 --> 01:45:56.718
THEY'D COME FROM ALL AROUND
TO HEAR BABY SUGGS HOLY--

01:45:56.751 --> 01:46:02.089
I SEEN AND HEARD THINGS
I AIN'T NEVER SEEN BEFORE.

01:46:04.125 --> 01:46:09.130
I SEEN WHAT FREE NEGROES
LOOK LIKE FOR THE FIRST TIME.

01:46:10.465 --> 01:46:15.903
HERE IN THIS PLACE,
WE ARE FLESH.

01:46:15.937 --> 01:46:19.040
FLESH THAT WEEPS...

01:46:19.073 --> 01:46:21.042
LAUGHS...

01:46:21.075 --> 01:46:23.778
DANCES BAREFOOT
IN THE GRASS.

01:46:23.811 --> 01:46:27.014
[ Audience Murmuring Approval ]

01:46:27.048 --> 01:46:30.652
LOVE YOUR FLESH.

01:46:31.886 --> 01:46:34.121
LOVE IT HARD.

01:46:34.155 --> 01:46:39.894
YONDER...
THEY DO NOT LOVE OUR FLESH.

01:46:39.927 --> 01:46:43.197
[ Man ]
AMEN.

01:46:43.230 --> 01:46:48.636
[ Chuckling ]
OH, MY PEOPLE...

01:46:50.071 --> 01:46:54.175
THEY DO NOT LOVE YOUR HANDS.

01:46:55.743 --> 01:47:01.449
THOSE...
THEY ONLY USE...

01:47:01.483 --> 01:47:04.986
TIE... BIND...

01:47:05.019 --> 01:47:07.221
CHOP OFF...

01:47:07.254 --> 01:47:10.492
AND LEAVE EMPTY.

01:47:12.860 --> 01:47:15.763
LOVE YOUR HANDS.

01:47:19.200 --> 01:47:22.069
RAISE THEM UP...

01:47:22.103 --> 01:47:24.271
AND KISS THEM.

01:47:26.107 --> 01:47:28.075
[ Kissing ]

01:47:28.109 --> 01:47:30.778
[ Guffawing ]

01:47:30.812 --> 01:47:35.249
[ All Laughing, Clapping ]

01:47:35.282 --> 01:47:40.488
TWENTY-EIGHT DAYS
OF... FREEDOM.

01:47:42.056 --> 01:47:45.359
ON THE 29th DAY,
IT WAS OVER.

01:47:53.067 --> 01:47:54.569
[ Chopping ]

01:47:56.738 --> 01:47:59.574
[ Whispering ]
OUTSIDE.

01:48:04.178 --> 01:48:06.147
[ Baby Crying ]

01:48:06.180 --> 01:48:08.583
[ Chopping Continues ]

01:48:14.656 --> 01:48:18.593
* [ Humming ]
[ Crying Continues ]

01:48:35.677 --> 01:48:40.715
[ Sethe Narrating ]
THERE'S A LOOK
THAT WHITE FOLKS GET.

01:48:40.748 --> 01:48:45.620
RIGHTEOUS LOOK THAT'S LIKE
A FLAG GOIN' UP A POLE.

01:48:47.889 --> 01:48:50.524
A RIGHTEOUSNESS THAT...

01:48:50.558 --> 01:48:54.095
COMES ALONG WITH THE WHIP
AND THE FIST,

01:48:54.128 --> 01:48:57.431
THE BURNIN', THE LIE.

01:48:57.464 --> 01:49:01.102
LONG BEFORE IT HAPPENS
IN THE OPEN.

01:49:01.135 --> 01:49:03.905
NO, NO !

01:49:03.938 --> 01:49:08.209
HOWARD, BUGLAR,
GET IN THE SHED !
[ Crying ]

01:49:08.242 --> 01:49:12.346
GET IN THE SHED ! RUN !

01:49:12.379 --> 01:49:14.616
[ Crying Continues ]

01:49:15.983 --> 01:49:18.285
[ Screaming ] NO !

01:49:18.319 --> 01:49:21.889
GET IN THE SHED ! NO !

01:49:23.157 --> 01:49:29.063
[ Sethe, Distant ]
NO ! NO ! NO ! NO !

01:49:29.096 --> 01:49:31.332
[ Sethe Continues Screaming ]

01:49:34.669 --> 01:49:37.605
[ Whinnying ]

01:49:37.639 --> 01:49:43.577
[ Screaming Hysterically ]
NO, NO, NO !

01:49:43.611 --> 01:49:47.982
- [ Sethe ]
NO, NO, NO !
-[ Boy ] MAMA !

01:49:48.015 --> 01:49:50.551
[ Boys Screaming ]

01:49:50.584 --> 01:49:53.454
[ Boy Screaming, Crying ]
MAMA !

01:49:53.487 --> 01:49:57.859
[ Screaming, Crying Continue ]

01:50:02.864 --> 01:50:04.598
[ Baby Crying ]

01:50:04.632 --> 01:50:06.968
[ Grunting ]
SETHE ! SETHE ! NO !

01:50:07.001 --> 01:50:10.838
SETHE !
[ Screaming ]

01:50:10.872 --> 01:50:13.307
[ Sethe Panting ]

01:50:13.340 --> 01:50:16.143
[ Coughing, Crying ]

01:50:16.177 --> 01:50:18.445
GOD ALMIGHTY.

01:50:18.479 --> 01:50:21.382
[ Denver Crying ]

01:50:27.554 --> 01:50:30.591
WHAT'D YOU GO
AND DO THAT FOR ?

01:50:30.624 --> 01:50:33.928
WHAT'D YOU GO
AND DO THAT FOR ?

01:50:33.961 --> 01:50:37.231
[ Breathing Heavily ]

01:50:39.400 --> 01:50:42.670
WHAT'D YOU GO
AND DO THAT FOR ?

01:50:48.142 --> 01:50:51.345
[ Denver Continues Crying ]

01:50:58.085 --> 01:50:59.721
[ Gasping ]

01:50:59.754 --> 01:51:04.726
Y'ALL BETTER GO ON.
NOTHIN' HERE TO CLAIM,
I GUESS.

01:51:04.759 --> 01:51:08.595
LOOK LIKE YOUR BUSINESS
IS OVER.
[ Throwing Hat ]

01:51:09.496 --> 01:51:11.332
MINE'S STARTED.

01:51:12.934 --> 01:51:14.869
[ Spits ]

01:51:14.902 --> 01:51:17.238
ANIMAL.

01:51:17.271 --> 01:51:20.341
[ Crying Continues ]

01:51:28.883 --> 01:51:30.684
[ Baby Suggs Gasping ]

01:51:30.718 --> 01:51:34.088
OH.
[ Continues Gasping ]

01:51:34.121 --> 01:51:36.290
OH.

01:51:38.192 --> 01:51:43.731
- OH.
- I'M GOING OUT.
I'LL SEND FOR A WAGON.

01:51:43.765 --> 01:51:47.601
HOWARD, HOWARD !
[ Wheezing ]

01:51:47.634 --> 01:51:50.772
- WAKE UP. BUGLAR. BABY !
- [ Buglar Wheezing ]

01:51:50.805 --> 01:51:53.775
COME ON, SWEETHEART.
WAKE UP ! WAKE UP !

01:51:53.808 --> 01:51:55.943
[ Moaning ]
OH !

01:51:55.977 --> 01:51:58.012
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

01:51:58.045 --> 01:52:02.784
SETHE, YOU TAKE MY ARMLOAD
AND GIVE ME YOUR'N.

01:52:02.817 --> 01:52:07.121
[ Boys Coughing ]
[ Crying ]

01:52:07.154 --> 01:52:12.960
[ Baby Suggs ]
I BEG YOUR PARDON.
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

01:52:12.994 --> 01:52:16.430
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

01:52:18.099 --> 01:52:21.402
YOUR LOVE
IS TOO THICK, SETHE.

01:52:22.503 --> 01:52:25.807
LOVE IS OR IT ISN'T,
PAUL D.

01:52:25.840 --> 01:52:28.943
THIN LOVE
AIN'T NO LOVE AT ALL.

01:52:28.976 --> 01:52:31.278
I STOPPED HIM.

01:52:31.312 --> 01:52:34.816
I PUT MY BABIES
WHERE'D THEY BE SAFE.

01:52:34.849 --> 01:52:38.085
DIDN'T WORK, THOUGH,
DID IT ?

01:52:38.119 --> 01:52:41.488
YOUR BOYS ARE GONE,
YOU DON'T KNOW WHERE.

01:52:41.522 --> 01:52:47.594
ONE GIRL'S DEAD.
THE OTHER CAN'T GET
FURTHER THAN THE YARD.

01:52:48.629 --> 01:52:51.098
HOW DID IT WORK ?

01:52:52.199 --> 01:52:54.802
THEY AIN'T AT SWEET HOME.

01:52:54.836 --> 01:52:57.438
SCHOOLTEACHER AIN'T GOT 'EM.

01:52:57.471 --> 01:53:01.909
MAYBE THERE'S WORSE.
IT AIN'T MY JOB TO KNOW
WHAT'S WORSE, PAUL D.

01:53:01.943 --> 01:53:07.114
IT'S MY JOB TO KNOW WHAT IS AND
KEEP MY CHILDREN AWAY FROM IT,
'CAUSE I'D RATHER KNOW...

01:53:07.148 --> 01:53:10.952
THEY AT PEACE IN HEAVEN
THAN LIVE IN A HELL HERE
ON EARTH, SO HELP ME, JESUS.

01:53:10.985 --> 01:53:14.788
WHAT YOU DID WAS WRONG, SETHE.
I SHOULD'VE
GONE BACK THERE ?

01:53:14.822 --> 01:53:18.125
TOOK MY BABIES
BACK TO SWEET HOME ?

01:53:18.159 --> 01:53:20.962
THERE COULD'VE BEEN A WAY.
SOME OTHER WAY.

01:53:20.995 --> 01:53:22.830
WHAT WAY, PAUL D ?

01:53:22.864 --> 01:53:27.068
YOU GOT TWO FEET,
SETHE, NOT FOUR.

01:53:35.242 --> 01:53:38.512
YOU CAN SET ASIDE SUPPER
FOR ME.

01:53:42.917 --> 01:53:46.988
I MIGHT BE LATE
GETTIN' BACK.

01:53:49.857 --> 01:53:54.095
AFTER ALL
I JUST TOLD YOU, PAUL D,

01:53:55.930 --> 01:53:59.400
AND AFTER YOU TELLIN' ME
HOW MANY FEET I GOT,

01:53:59.433 --> 01:54:04.705
YOU THINK SAYIN' GOOD-BYE
IS GONNA BREAK ME INTO PIECES ?

01:54:11.412 --> 01:54:14.181
YOU'RE A SWEET MAN.

01:54:24.959 --> 01:54:27.929
[ Door Shutting ]

01:54:27.962 --> 01:54:30.965
SO LONG, PAUL D.

01:54:47.915 --> 01:54:50.451
WE COULD ROAST
SOME TATERS.

01:54:50.484 --> 01:54:54.555
TOO LATE.
TOMORROW.

01:55:11.238 --> 01:55:15.076
* [ Humming Lullaby ]

01:55:19.146 --> 01:55:22.016
* [ Continues ]

01:55:34.128 --> 01:55:36.030
* [ Stops ]

01:55:37.264 --> 01:55:40.067
I MADE THAT SONG UP.

01:55:40.101 --> 01:55:44.005
I MADE IT UP AND SANG IT
TO MY CHILDREN.

01:55:44.038 --> 01:55:46.840
NOBODY KNOWS THAT SONG BUT...

01:55:48.542 --> 01:55:51.112
ME AND MY CHILDREN.

01:55:52.479 --> 01:55:55.116
I KNOW.

01:55:55.149 --> 01:55:58.552
* [ Resumes Humming ]

01:56:18.305 --> 01:56:22.576
[ Muffled Humming,
Wheezing ]

01:56:52.539 --> 01:56:54.708
[ Gasping ]

01:57:02.283 --> 01:57:05.386
YOU CAME BACK TO ME.

01:57:08.355 --> 01:57:11.125
[ Softly ]
YEAH.

01:57:50.631 --> 01:57:55.769
[ Beloved Snoring,
Wheezing ]
OHH.

01:57:55.802 --> 01:58:00.474
BACK STIFF ?
MMM. YEAH.

01:58:00.507 --> 01:58:04.778
SLEEPING ON THE FLOOR'S SUPPOSED
TO BE GOOD FOR YOU.
HURT LIKE THE DEVIL.

01:58:04.811 --> 01:58:07.314
SHOULD I WAKE HER ?

01:58:07.348 --> 01:58:09.983
NO. LET HER REST.

01:58:10.016 --> 01:58:12.419
SHE LIKES TO SEE YOU OFF
IN THE MORNING.

01:58:12.453 --> 01:58:15.489
I'M GONNA LET HER,
BUT FIRST GET ME THAT HAM
OUT OF THERE.

01:58:15.522 --> 01:58:19.926
I'M GONNA MAKE US
A NICE, BIG BREAKFAST
AGAINST THE COLD OUTSIDE.

01:58:19.960 --> 01:58:23.964
WON'T YOU BE LATE FOR WORK ?
FIRST TIME I'LL BE LATE
IN 16 YEARS.

01:58:23.997 --> 01:58:25.766
IT DON'T MATTER.

01:58:25.799 --> 01:58:27.301
WHATEVER GOES ON OUT THERE

01:58:27.334 --> 01:58:29.670
GOES ON WITH OR WITHOUT ME
SHOWIN' UP ON TIME.

01:58:29.703 --> 01:58:31.672
THE WORLD IS RIGHT HERE
IN THIS ROOM.

01:58:31.705 --> 01:58:36.610
RIGHT HERE IS ALL THAT IS
AND ALL THERE NEEDS TO BE.
[ Stirring ]

01:58:36.643 --> 01:58:42.516
SHE AIN'T EVEN MAD
AT ME. NOT A BIT.
[ Continues Wheezing ]

01:58:42.549 --> 01:58:45.152
[ Groaning ]

01:58:53.126 --> 01:58:56.230
[ Girls Chattering, Distant ]

01:58:59.200 --> 01:59:01.368
[ Chuckling ]

01:59:02.803 --> 01:59:05.406
WHOO.

01:59:19.553 --> 01:59:23.757
[ Boy #1 ]
MAMA !
[ Boy #2 ]
MAMA !

01:59:26.727 --> 01:59:28.295
MAMA !
MAMA !

01:59:28.329 --> 01:59:32.399
[ Footsteps Crunching
In Snow ]

01:59:33.834 --> 01:59:36.503
MAMA !
MAMA !

01:59:47.614 --> 01:59:49.950
[ Chattering ]

01:59:55.922 --> 01:59:58.692
[ Man ]
PUT IT BACK IN THERE.
PUT IT BACK.

01:59:58.725 --> 02:00:01.762
[ Speaking German ]
THAT'S IT. YOU'RE LATE.
YOU'RE FIRED.

02:00:01.795 --> 02:00:03.830
THAT'S ALL.
I-I-- I'VE HAD IT.

02:00:03.864 --> 02:00:07.100
YOU MAKE POTATO SALAD
ALWAYS TOO SWEET.

02:00:07.133 --> 02:00:09.536
AND YOU DIDN'T MAKE
THE PIES TODAY.

02:00:09.570 --> 02:00:13.974
YOU TAKE HOME TOO MUCH FOOD.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING ?
WHERE ARE YOU GOING ?

02:01:03.957 --> 02:01:08.028
MY GOODNESS.
IS THAT--
YES, IT IS.

02:01:12.799 --> 02:01:16.970
DID YOU SEE THAT ?
WHAT ?
THAT'S A DISGRACE.

02:01:19.873 --> 02:01:22.543
[ Chattering ]

02:01:26.347 --> 02:01:28.349
SETHE.

02:01:28.382 --> 02:01:31.518
[ Woman ]
DON'T LOOK NOW,
BUT THERE IS SETHE.

02:01:42.563 --> 02:01:45.065
MM.
IS SHE THE ONE ?

02:02:02.148 --> 02:02:05.051
WILL THAT BE ALL, MA'AM ?

02:02:05.085 --> 02:02:07.621
[ All Screaming ]

02:02:07.654 --> 02:02:09.890
[ Women ]
* TO GET MY GRIP
[ Screaming ]

02:02:09.923 --> 02:02:13.794
* I CAME BACK HOME
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF *

02:02:13.827 --> 02:02:16.563
* WENT UPSTAIRS
TO MAKE MY BED *

02:02:16.597 --> 02:02:19.733
* I MADE A MISTAKE
AND BUMPED MY HEAD *

02:02:19.766 --> 02:02:22.869
* JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF *

02:02:22.903 --> 02:02:26.540
[ Together ]
* I CAME DOWNSTAIRS
TO MILK THAT COW *

02:02:26.573 --> 02:02:29.676
* I MADE A MISTAKE
AND I MILKED THAT SOW *

02:02:29.710 --> 02:02:33.313
* JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF
JUST A-PULLIN' THE SKIFF *

02:02:33.346 --> 02:02:36.082
[ Screeching, Laughing ]
* TOMORROW, TOMORROW
TOMORROW NEVER COMES *

02:02:36.116 --> 02:02:39.520
* TOMORROW, TOMORROW
TOMORROW NEVER COMES *

02:02:39.553 --> 02:02:42.756
[ Denver ]
THE BEST PART.
* [ All Grunting In Tune ]

02:02:42.789 --> 02:02:46.593
* [ Grunting Continues ]
[ Beloved Babbling ]

02:02:46.627 --> 02:02:50.263
LOOK AT MY PRETTY BABY.
SHE'S MY BEST THING.
DENVER.

02:02:50.296 --> 02:02:52.666
[ Beloved ]
* TOMORROW NEVER COME

02:02:52.699 --> 02:02:56.837
THANK YOU, MAMA.
* TOMORROW, TOMORROW
TOMORROW IN THE BARN *

02:02:56.870 --> 02:03:00.641
[ Laughing ]
* [ Grunting ]

02:03:10.484 --> 02:03:13.654
[ Beloved Babbling ]

02:03:27.968 --> 02:03:29.636
THIS ONE ?

02:03:29.670 --> 02:03:33.640
WOULD YOU WRAP IT,
PLEASE ?
WHAT'S SHE DOING ?

02:03:47.688 --> 02:03:49.590
[ Sethe Panting ]

02:03:49.623 --> 02:03:52.559
THE FIRST DAY WE GOT HERE
TO BLUESTONE ROAD,

02:03:52.593 --> 02:03:54.961
YOU DRIBBLED CLEAR SPIT
ON MY FACE.

02:03:54.995 --> 02:03:58.665
JUST LIKE WHEN YOU COME BACK
AND DRINK THAT WATER,

02:03:58.699 --> 02:04:00.501
IT RUN DOWN YOUR CHIN.

02:04:00.534 --> 02:04:02.803
I'D HAVE RECOGNIZED YOU
RIGHT OFF,

02:04:02.836 --> 02:04:06.006
[ Beloved Grunting ]
BUT PAUL D,
HE DISTRACT ME.

02:04:06.039 --> 02:04:07.508
THEN LATER ON,

02:04:07.541 --> 02:04:10.844
WHEN YOU ASKED ME ABOUT
THEM EARRINGS I USED TO DANGLE

02:04:10.877 --> 02:04:12.513
FOR YOU TO PLAY WITH,

02:04:12.546 --> 02:04:15.782
[ Babbling ]
I'D HAVE KNOWN
THAT WAS YOU,

02:04:15.816 --> 02:04:19.119
EXCEPT FOR PAUL D.

02:04:19.152 --> 02:04:22.188
LOOKED TO ME LIKE
HE WANTED YOU OUT
FROM THE BEGINNING.

02:04:22.222 --> 02:04:26.026
BUT I WOULDN'T LET HIM.
WHAT YOU THINK ?

02:04:26.059 --> 02:04:27.928
HMM.

02:04:27.961 --> 02:04:29.630
I MEAN, LOOK HOW HE RUN OFF

02:04:29.663 --> 02:04:33.967
FIRST HE HEAR ABOUT
YOU AND ME IN THE SHED.

02:04:34.000 --> 02:04:37.871
TOO TOUGH FOR HIM
TO EVEN LISTEN TO.

02:04:37.904 --> 02:04:41.542
"MY LOVE TOO THICK," HE SAID.

02:04:41.575 --> 02:04:44.477
WHAT DO HE KNOW
ABOUT IT ?

02:04:44.511 --> 02:04:47.047
[ Sethe ]
* HIGH JOHNNY

02:04:47.080 --> 02:04:49.349
* WIDE JOHNNY

02:04:49.382 --> 02:04:53.319
* DON'T YOU LEAVE MY SIDE

02:04:53.353 --> 02:04:56.790
* HIGH JOHNNY

02:04:56.823 --> 02:04:59.392
* WIDE JOHNNY

02:04:59.425 --> 02:05:05.599
* SWEET WILLIAM
BEND DOWN LOW *

02:05:07.834 --> 02:05:12.072
- * JACK, WE RAISE UP HIGH
- [ Beloved Laughs ]

02:05:12.105 --> 02:05:16.810
* LAMBS WOOL
WHY YOU HURT ME ?

02:05:16.843 --> 02:05:20.714
BABY, YOU KNOW.

02:05:20.747 --> 02:05:23.817
WHY YOU LEAVE ME ?

02:05:23.850 --> 02:05:27.020
BELOVED, I WASN'T NEVER
GONNA LEAVE YOU.

02:05:27.053 --> 02:05:28.589
NEVER.

02:05:28.622 --> 02:05:31.091
BUT THERE WASN'T NO WAY
I WAS GONNA LET SCHOOLTEACHER

02:05:31.124 --> 02:05:32.525
COME HAUL ALL OF US OFF...

02:05:32.559 --> 02:05:35.428
AND MEASURE YOUR BEHIND
'FORE HE TORE IT UP.

02:05:35.461 --> 02:05:38.431
- YOU LEAVE ME.
- NO, BABY. NO.

02:05:38.464 --> 02:05:43.536
SEE, MY PLAN WAS TO GET US
ALL OVER TO THE OTHER SIDE
WHERE MY OWN MAMMY IS.

02:05:43.570 --> 02:05:47.173
THEY STOPPED ME
FROM GETTIN' US ALL THERE,
BUT YOU HAD TO BE PUT...

02:05:47.207 --> 02:05:50.376
WHERE YOU'D BE SAFE,
AND I DID THAT.

02:05:51.244 --> 02:05:53.013
NOW YOU COME BACK,

02:05:53.046 --> 02:05:56.583
AND BABY, I AIN'T GONNA
NEVER LET YOU GO.

02:05:56.617 --> 02:05:58.585
I WANT A SWEET.

02:05:58.619 --> 02:06:01.121
SWEET ?

02:06:01.154 --> 02:06:03.590
[ Moaning, Grunting ]
SWEET.

02:06:03.624 --> 02:06:06.259
WE DON'T HAVE NOTHIN' SWEET
NO MORE, BABY.

02:06:06.292 --> 02:06:09.896
WHY YOU DON'T LET ME
EAT THE PIE NO MORE ?

02:06:09.930 --> 02:06:11.965
[ Plate Crashing ]

02:06:11.998 --> 02:06:15.802
[ Moaning ]
SINCE MAMA SPENT ALL THE
MONEY,WE DON'T HAVE NO MORE.

02:06:15.836 --> 02:06:19.773
[ Screaming ]
I WANT A SWEET !
I WANT A SWEET !

02:06:19.806 --> 02:06:23.443
SWEET, SWEET, SWEET !
BELOVED ? BELOVED !

02:06:23.476 --> 02:06:27.313
- [ Screaming Continues ]
-[ Sethe ]
BELOVED, BABY ?

02:06:27.347 --> 02:06:29.883
BABY ? BELOVED !

02:06:29.916 --> 02:06:34.187
[ Screaming,
Crying ]

02:06:36.422 --> 02:06:39.259
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

02:06:41.361 --> 02:06:45.565
[ Gasping ]
I UNDERSTAND.

02:06:45.598 --> 02:06:49.435
[ Buzzing ]
[ Whimpering ]

02:07:06.152 --> 02:07:09.322
[ Buzzing Continues ]

02:07:14.227 --> 02:07:16.897
[ Chirping ]

02:07:23.303 --> 02:07:25.906
[ Moaning ]

02:07:30.310 --> 02:07:32.913
[ Gagging ]

02:07:36.216 --> 02:07:39.419
[ Screeching ]

02:07:43.389 --> 02:07:46.026
[ Screeching Continues ]

02:07:46.059 --> 02:07:48.028
BELOVED ?

02:07:52.365 --> 02:07:55.936
[ Crying ]

02:08:02.776 --> 02:08:04.945
[ Buzzing ]

02:08:07.781 --> 02:08:09.950
[ Birds Chirping ]

02:08:19.125 --> 02:08:21.461
[ Clucking ]

02:08:54.795 --> 02:08:58.999
[ Clanking ]
[ Beloved Screaming ]

02:09:08.674 --> 02:09:12.813
[ Glass Breaking ]
[ Beloved Screaming ]

02:09:20.787 --> 02:09:23.023
MAMA !

02:09:24.791 --> 02:09:28.494
[ Footsteps Above ]
MAMA !

02:09:28.528 --> 02:09:31.331
[ Metal Clanking ]
[ Babbling ]

02:09:31.364 --> 02:09:33.266
[ Groaning ]

02:09:33.299 --> 02:09:36.036
[ Babbling Continues ]

02:09:46.779 --> 02:09:49.615
MAMA !

02:09:49.649 --> 02:09:54.287
[ Rattling ]
[ Screaming, Babbling ]

02:09:54.320 --> 02:09:56.556
MAMA !

02:10:00.293 --> 02:10:02.528
MAMA !

02:10:05.031 --> 02:10:08.001
[ Babbling Resumes ]

02:10:18.244 --> 02:10:22.515
YOU BEST LEAVE
THAT QUILT ALONE.

02:10:22.548 --> 02:10:25.418
THAT'S GRANDMA'S QUILT.

02:10:28.354 --> 02:10:30.590
[ Gasping ]

02:10:37.998 --> 02:10:43.036
[ Babbling ]
I WANT A SWEET.
WHERE IS SWEET ?

02:10:49.075 --> 02:10:52.045
[ Clattering, Distant ]

02:10:59.252 --> 02:11:02.622
[ Chattering, Distant ]

02:11:20.907 --> 02:11:26.046
[ Baby Suggs ]
YOU MEAN I NEVER TELL YOU
ABOUT YOUR DADDY, HALLE ?

02:11:26.079 --> 02:11:29.950
HOW HE BOUGHT MY FREEDOM
WITH ALL THAT TOIL...

02:11:29.983 --> 02:11:35.956
AND NEVER HAD A CHANCE
TO SEE THE PROMISED LAND
FOR HISSELF ?

02:11:35.989 --> 02:11:40.360
DIDN'T I TELL YOU
ABOUT THE BODWINS,

02:11:40.393 --> 02:11:43.263
WHO FIND ME
THIS HERE HOUSE...

02:11:43.296 --> 02:11:45.932
AND GIVE ME WORK
IN THEIRS ?

02:11:45.966 --> 02:11:52.305
HOW THE BODWINS,
THEY SAVED YOUR MAMA'S NECK
FROM THE ROPE.

02:11:52.338 --> 02:11:56.909
I NEVER TELL YOU ALL THIS ?

02:11:56.943 --> 02:12:00.713
IS THAT WHY YOU SCARED...

02:12:00.746 --> 02:12:04.317
TO GO DOWN THEM STEPS
AND OUT YONDER...

02:12:04.350 --> 02:12:06.987
BY YOURSELF ?

02:12:07.020 --> 02:12:10.156
IS THAT WHY
YOU DIDN'T GO BACK
TO MISS LADY...

02:12:10.190 --> 02:12:12.825
AND FINISH LEARNIN'
YOUR LETTERS ?

02:12:12.858 --> 02:12:16.662
YOU LIKED GOING THERE.
I REMEMBER.

02:12:16.696 --> 02:12:23.003
BEIN' WITH THE OTHER CHILDREN.
ALL OF A SUDDEN YOU'VE STOPPED.

02:12:25.705 --> 02:12:28.541
THERE WAS THIS BOY...

02:12:29.809 --> 02:12:32.645
AND HE SAID THINGS
ABOUT MAMA.

02:12:32.678 --> 02:12:35.848
[ Gasping ]
HE SAID
HE COULD PROVE IT.

02:12:35.881 --> 02:12:40.053
[ Wheezing ]
MY JESUS, MY.

02:12:41.554 --> 02:12:44.224
COME HERE, CHILD.

02:12:51.831 --> 02:12:54.634
WE GOT TO GO
SOMETIME.

02:12:54.667 --> 02:13:00.306
YOU GOT TO GO OUT YONDER
BY YOURSELF SOMETIME.

02:13:02.008 --> 02:13:05.878
YOU GOT TO GO ON
OUT OF THE YARD.

02:13:05.911 --> 02:13:08.581
GO ON.

02:14:30.296 --> 02:14:33.099
[ Hammering ]

02:14:34.800 --> 02:14:37.403
[ Chattering ]

02:14:43.976 --> 02:14:46.679
[ Man ]
COME ON, NOW.

02:14:58.591 --> 02:15:01.161
[ Denver ]
I WANT TO WORK, MISS LADY.

02:15:02.262 --> 02:15:04.297
WORK ?

02:15:04.330 --> 02:15:07.833
START LEARNIN'
YOUR LETTERS AGAIN ?

02:15:10.002 --> 02:15:13.139
I MEAN "WORK" WORK.

02:15:14.807 --> 02:15:16.442
WELL, DENVER,

02:15:17.843 --> 02:15:20.380
WHAT CAN YOU DO ?

02:15:25.718 --> 02:15:27.787
I CAN'T DO NOTHIN'.

02:15:27.820 --> 02:15:32.892
BUT I COULD LEARN IT FOR YOU...
IF YOU HAVE A LITTLE EXTRA.

02:15:35.127 --> 02:15:37.029
EXTRA ?

02:15:39.732 --> 02:15:41.734
FOOD.

02:15:46.806 --> 02:15:48.474
MY MAMA...

02:15:50.510 --> 02:15:53.979
SHE DON'T FEEL TOO GOOD.

02:15:54.847 --> 02:15:57.917
[ Sighs ]
OH, BABY.

02:16:12.898 --> 02:16:16.402
EAT. BAD SETHE.

02:16:16.436 --> 02:16:20.240
YES. BAD SETHE.

02:16:25.778 --> 02:16:28.748
[ Beloved Babbling ]

02:16:28.781 --> 02:16:32.418
[ Beloved ]
EAT.

02:16:32.451 --> 02:16:34.520
EAT.

02:17:03.648 --> 02:17:05.985
[ Chirping ]

02:17:08.821 --> 02:17:11.391
OHH, HONEY.

02:17:11.424 --> 02:17:13.925
WHAT YOU GOT ?

02:17:30.174 --> 02:17:32.812
[ Gasping ]
THANK YOU, MA'AM.

02:17:32.844 --> 02:17:36.316
YOU'RE MORE THAN WELCOME,
MY CHILD.

02:17:51.364 --> 02:17:53.532
THANK YOU.

02:17:55.468 --> 02:17:59.103
[ Woman ]
NO, NO. THAT'S NOT MY BOWL.

02:17:59.138 --> 02:18:01.272
SUGAR, MINE GOT
A BLUE RING ON IT.

02:18:01.307 --> 02:18:03.609
YOU WANNA
COME IN A SPELL ?
COME ON IN.

02:18:03.643 --> 02:18:08.548
I GOT SOME WARM GINGERBREAD.
YOU JUST GO ON IN THERE.
OKAY.

02:18:14.887 --> 02:18:17.289
[ Rooster Crowing ]

02:18:21.960 --> 02:18:24.564
[ Chattering ]

02:18:46.419 --> 02:18:48.821
[ Dog Barking ]

02:18:48.853 --> 02:18:53.225
SHH. SHH. GO ON.
MOVE. GET OFF OF ME.

02:18:53.258 --> 02:18:57.730
- YOU STINK, AND YOU MESSIN'
UP MY DRESS. STOP IT.
- [ Barking Continues ]

02:18:57.763 --> 02:19:00.799
I'M TELLIN' YOU,
GET OFF OF ME.
GET OFF OF ME, NOW !

02:19:00.833 --> 02:19:03.636
[ Grunting ]
STOP IT.
[ Growling ]

02:19:03.669 --> 02:19:07.406
- HOW FAR YOU GOIN', MISS ?
- I GOIN' TO CINCINNATI.

02:19:11.911 --> 02:19:17.281
[ Driver ] THAT'S AS FAR AS
WE'RE GOIN', MISS. GET OFF.
THANK YOU.

02:19:18.784 --> 02:19:22.087
HOW'S IT GOIN' ?
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF,
ALL RIGHT ?

02:19:22.120 --> 02:19:26.058
EXCUSE ME. I WAS LOOKIN'
FOR THE BODWIN'S HOUSE.

02:19:26.091 --> 02:19:30.596
YOU BUGGER OFF,
YOU HEAR ME ?

02:19:30.629 --> 02:19:33.466
[ Chattering ]

02:19:46.378 --> 02:19:48.481
YES ?

02:19:52.652 --> 02:19:55.087
WHAT YOU WANT ?

02:19:57.322 --> 02:20:02.695
I WANTED TO SEE
MR. AND MRS. BOWMAN--
MR. AND MRS. BODWIN.

02:20:02.728 --> 02:20:04.764
MS. BODWIN.

02:20:04.797 --> 02:20:08.968
THEY BROTHER
AND SISTER, DARLIN'.
WHAT YOU WANT WITH 'EM ?

02:20:09.001 --> 02:20:11.804
I WAS LOOKIN' FOR WORK,

02:20:11.837 --> 02:20:14.774
AND I THOUGHT THAT
THEY MIGHT KNOW ABOUT SOME.

02:20:16.308 --> 02:20:18.644
OHH...

02:20:18.678 --> 02:20:21.647
YOU BABY SUGGS' KID,
AIN'T YOU ?

02:20:21.681 --> 02:20:26.452
[ Chuckling ]
YES'M.
I HEARD
YOUR MOTHER TOOK SICK.

02:20:26.486 --> 02:20:31.657
IS THAT SO ?
YES'M.

02:20:31.691 --> 02:20:37.296
WELL, COME ON IN.
YOU'RE LETTIN' IN FLIES.
COME ON.

02:20:37.329 --> 02:20:42.902
YOU KNOW WHAT ? I BEEN HERE
SINCE I WAS 14, AND I CAN
REMEMBER LIKE YESTERDAY...

02:20:42.935 --> 02:20:47.239
WHEN BABY SUGGS HOLY CAME HERE
AND SAT RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.

02:20:47.272 --> 02:20:52.344
WHITE MAN, NAME OF GARNER,
BROUGHT HER. HE AND MR. BODWIN
WAS GOOD FRIENDS.

02:20:52.377 --> 02:20:57.182
THAT'S HOW SHE GOT
THAT HOUSE YOU ALL LIVE IN.
OTHER THINGS TOO.
YES'M.

02:20:57.216 --> 02:21:02.354
I NEVER WENT
TO THOSE WOODLAND SERVICES,
BUT SHE WAS ALWAYS NICE TO ME.

02:21:02.387 --> 02:21:06.191
ALWAYS.
NEVER BE ANOTHER LIKE HER.

02:21:06.225 --> 02:21:07.960
I MISS HER.

02:21:07.993 --> 02:21:14.066
BET YOU DO.
EVERYBODY MISS HER.
THAT WAS A GOOD WOMAN.

02:21:15.467 --> 02:21:17.202
WELL...

02:21:17.236 --> 02:21:20.005
I DON'T KNOW WHETHER
THE BODWINS THINK SO OR NOT,

02:21:20.039 --> 02:21:22.508
BUT THEY SURE
COULD USE SOME EXTRA HELP.

02:21:22.542 --> 02:21:24.810
[ Both Chuckling ]
YOU THINK ?

02:21:24.844 --> 02:21:28.347
ESPECIALLY AT NIGHT,
WHEN IT'S NO GOOD
FOR ME TO COME.

02:21:28.380 --> 02:21:32.685
IT'LL TAKE SOME CONVINCIN',
BUT MAYBE YOU COULD COME
AFTER SUPPER.

02:21:32.718 --> 02:21:37.056
TAKE CARE OF YOUR MAMA
DURING THE DAY.
HOW'S THAT ?

02:21:37.089 --> 02:21:40.225
FINE.
[ Chuckling ]

02:21:40.259 --> 02:21:42.061
BUT WHAT WOULD I DO
AT NIGHT ?

02:21:42.094 --> 02:21:46.231
JUST BE HERE
IN CASE.
IN CASE WHAT ?

02:21:46.265 --> 02:21:51.804
IN CASE THE HOUSE BURNED DOWN OR
BAD WEATHER SLOPPED THE ROADS UP
SO BAD I CAN'T GET HERE ON TIME.

02:21:51.837 --> 02:21:54.206
OR LATE GUESTS NEEDED
CLEANIN' UP AFTER.

02:21:54.239 --> 02:21:56.008
ANYTHING.

02:21:56.041 --> 02:22:01.681
[ Snickering ]
DON'T ASK ME WHAT
WHITE FOLKS NEED AT NIGHT.

02:22:01.714 --> 02:22:05.217
THEY GOOD WHITE FOLK ?
OH, YEAH. THEY GOOD.

02:22:05.250 --> 02:22:09.689
CAN'T SAY THEY AIN'T GOOD.
I WOULDN'T TRADE 'EM FOR
ANOTHER PAIR, I TELL YOU THAT.

02:22:09.722 --> 02:22:15.227
BUT YOU COME BACK IN A FEW DAYS.
GIVE ME A CHANCE
TO LEAD UP TO IT.

02:22:15.260 --> 02:22:16.862
ALL RIGHT ?

02:22:21.300 --> 02:22:25.037
WHAT IS IT, CHILD ?

02:22:25.070 --> 02:22:27.439
WHAT'S THE TROUBLE
WITH SETHE ?

02:22:30.810 --> 02:22:32.778
[ Whimpering ]

02:22:32.812 --> 02:22:34.814
[ Chattering ]

02:22:36.315 --> 02:22:39.451
IS IT REALLY
THE DAUGHTER, JANEY ?
THE KILLED ONE ?

02:22:39.484 --> 02:22:41.921
THAT'S WHAT
THE GIRL SAY.

02:22:41.954 --> 02:22:45.591
- HOW DO YOU KNOW IT'S HER ?
- IT'S SITTIN' THERE, LUCILLE.

02:22:45.625 --> 02:22:48.527
IT SLEEPS, EATS
AND RAISES HELL.

02:22:48.560 --> 02:22:51.196
I'LL BE. A BABY.
[ All Murmuring ]

02:22:51.230 --> 02:22:55.134
NAH. IT'S GROWN. IT'S
THE AGE IT WOULD'VE BEEN
HAD IT LIVED.

02:22:55.167 --> 02:22:58.270
MERCY.
WHAT YOU TALKIN' ABOUT ?
YOU TALKIN' ABOUT FLESH ?

02:22:58.303 --> 02:23:03.142
I'M TALKIN' ABOUT FLESH...
AND IT'S WHOOPIN' HER...
[ Women Gasping ]

02:23:03.175 --> 02:23:04.977
LIKE SHE WAS BATTER.

02:23:05.010 --> 02:23:10.582
- I GUESS SHE HAD IT COMIN'
A LITTLE.
- NOBODY GOT THAT COMIN'.

02:23:10.616 --> 02:23:15.621
BUT ELLA, YOU JUST DON'T UP
AND KILL YOUR CHILDREN.

02:23:15.655 --> 02:23:20.259
NO, AND THE CHILDREN
CAN'T JUST UP
AND KILL THE MAMA.

02:23:20.292 --> 02:23:23.829
THEM THAT DIE BAD
DON'T STAY IN THE GROUND.

02:23:23.863 --> 02:23:26.331
[ All Commenting ]

02:23:30.269 --> 02:23:32.304
[ Sethe Muttering ]

02:23:32.337 --> 02:23:35.207
[ Chopping ]

02:23:37.209 --> 02:23:39.845
[ Beloved Snorting ]

02:23:39.879 --> 02:23:42.982
[ Sethe ]
SCHOOLTEACHER--

02:23:43.015 --> 02:23:44.884
MAMA ?

02:23:46.151 --> 02:23:49.154
NOBODY AIN'T MAKIN' NOTHIN'.

02:23:49.188 --> 02:23:52.157
NOBODY.
MAMA, I'M GOING OUT NOW.

02:23:52.191 --> 02:23:54.326
[ Continues Muttering ]

02:23:54.359 --> 02:23:56.929
[ Chopping Continues ]

02:23:56.962 --> 02:24:01.867
I GOT A JOB WORKIN' NIGHTS
OVER AT THE BODWINS.

02:24:01.901 --> 02:24:05.738
MR. BODWIN'S COMING
TO PICK ME UP NOW.

02:24:07.206 --> 02:24:11.210
WRITIN' MY BABY'S
CHARACTERISTICS !
[ Grunts ]

02:24:11.243 --> 02:24:13.378
LAY THAT DOWN.

02:24:13.412 --> 02:24:16.982
WE HAVE MONEY NOW.

02:24:18.650 --> 02:24:21.987
[ Muttering Continues ]

02:24:22.021 --> 02:24:23.923
MAMA !

02:24:31.063 --> 02:24:32.331
[ Muttering ]

